messages: ['Hi Italy! Just opening up communication, and I want to know what some of your initial thoughts on the game are and if/how we can work together', "Well....that's a great question, and a lot of it comes down to how free I'll be left to play in the West, no?", 'Well, if you want to attack France in the Mediterranean while I attack through Burgundy you can have Marseille and Iberia while I take Brest and Paris, then with France out of the way you could focus on Turkey or Austria. Sound fair?', "Hello, I'm just asking about your move to Tyrolia. It's making me more than a little concerned", 'Totally understandable - but did you notice the attempt at Trieste?  Tyrolia is the natural support position for that attempt 🙂']
sender_labels: [True, True, True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, False, True, False]

messages: ["Hey Italy! What's your plan for the game?", 'Bongiorno!  To crush my enemies, see them driven before me, and hear the lamentations of their women!  I mean, umm, not really sure yet.  Pondering whether or not to make an early play around Munich', "I'd personally rather you didn't, because a play around Munich is also a play around Trieste and Vienna. I've heard that there's some rancor over in the West and you might be able to profit from a mobbed France if you went that way.", 'Good to know, thanks!', 'Well, that went well! Shall we push on with the ways we started?', 'Well, the West and East are both an unholy mess now.  Second fleet incoming, I assume you agree we need to nip that Turkish issue in the bud before it becomes unmanageable?', 'So...was that a no?', 'Indeed.', 'Peccato.  I was really hoping we could bring order (or at least mutual profit) out of the chaos.', "Sorry we couldn't patch things up."]
sender_labels: [True, True, False, True, True, True, True, True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, 'NOANNOTATION', True, True, True, True]

messages: ['Hey Italy! How’s it going?!', 'Hey hey, what can I say?', 'Hahha what’s good?', 'To crush your enemies, see them driven before you, and hear the lamentations of their women', 'Hahahah that’s the spirit sir!', 'Hey Italy - what’s good?']
sender_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True]

messages: ['Hello Italy, just wanted to thank you for your gift to the culinary world and wish you a good game!', 'Just to be clear, that was all in a pasta life.', 'From this one interaction alone I trust you. Please dont betray me and make me eat dish of regretti and meatballs.']
sender_labels: [True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True]

messages:
["We both hate how I vs T just slows us both down, right?  Why do we have to be the slow powers in this game?  I say: we don't!  Let's be unconventional.  I have done fun I/T alliances before, but it all depends on making it work.  Let me know if you have any thoughts, or want to just see how the first few seasons roll out, or if there are things you'd like to see from me.", "I mean, if I'm free to go another direction, I'll take it in a heartbeat - and I doubt you'll be very upset at my opening moves 🙂", 'His dots are closer to you. 😃', 'hahahahaha really?', "If Austria retreats to one of your centers, I guess it means they don't care about trying to repair anything with you, and Just Loves Them Dots, yeah?", "I may be able to hit Tri in the fall, which would cut it's ability to support Ven, by the way.  If Ion retreats to Adr, that may not help you, but if it retreats to Tun or Nap it would, I guess?  Let's see how the retreats go.", "So, now his dots are a LOT closer to you than mine are. 😃

I'm guessing you're ordering into Trieste anyway to protect Serbia while you take Greece with Bulgaria and Aegean. So the question is what is ion doing?", "It's at your disposal if you want support into Tunis, if that's what you're getting at.", "Oh, come now. It's much more amusing to support you into Tunis. That advances the positions rather than retards them", "Bwa! are you serious?  I'm not one to look a gift horse in the mouth, but I feel like I'm greedy enough stabbing Austria for 3!", "Any other arrangement opens me for a stab and sets us up for conflict. Tunis is better for you than Naples, and it's a lot better for me to have you there with a path forward than tied up with me. If you feel bad about it, support me to Trieste", "Ok, that's totally sensible logic.  I may end up having to pass up on Greece and catch it next year.  I can support you into Trieste, if you'd rather have that than retaking Venice, sure.", 'Oh nevermind, you can get both, nice!', 'unless Gre taps Ser, in which case you still recapture Ven, and Austria is stranded in Tri.', "Correct. Which is what I'm expecting, but I can hope for Trieste. 😀", "You heartless bastard - I can't believe you took him from 5 to 0.", 'It was kinder this way. Put ‘em out of their misery, y’know?', 'Lol. Probably. That is the great thing about Austria -you either do well or you get to go play another game.', 'Yep. I’m finishing up game 10 of this series now as Austria. Currently on 14 centers, but England has Tunis so no win for me 😦', "Ah, well.  
So, what's the plan from here?  How far are you planning on riding that juggernaut?", 'Well I want to see Russia moves hard on Germany. If they do, well I have a history of jumping on big openings, y’know? :). Otherwise fleets are heading toward Gibraltar!', 'Sounds fun!', "Also, weirdly, my phone doesn't seem to be updating me with latest messages the way it should, so I end up seeing these a lot later than I should", 'So I tried to move towards a more forward position so I could fight France an d stab Russia, and *not* fight you, but you’re kinda putting yourself directly in my way, y’know?', 'I could’ve kept you out of Ion permanently but that wasn’t what I thought was very interesting long term. :/', "Yeah, I wasn't seeing any response from you, so I moved to defend.  We're having some communication issues based on mis-timing, I think.  Cost us most of a turn, but we have the weekend to work out a way forward, nu?", 'Sure, understood.  How about this to fix it: Tys S Tun-Wes, Ion-Tun?  You take back a dot, but we push the position forwards toward Iberia?', 'are you still not getting any messages from me?', 'That could definitely work - and it does advance the positions', 'Otherwise this game is going to be a long, unpleasant slog', "I get your messages fine on the computer - it's the phone that seems to not update properly for some reason.  I just hadn't checked the computer yesterday as I should have 🙂", 'Ok, France has told me outright they're wanting to make sure that "Italy is divided fairly", so I doubt they'll expect me pushing past you toward the west.', 'Looks that way, yes', "It's too bad we can't find a way to work together to force me out into MAO, instead of whittling down your defenses season by season.  Once you lose a center, this is going to crumble really quickly, but I'd totally be willing to try something else, even though we both didn't do what we said we do last season.", "Aye, it's not a *great* plan to just turtle up and try to outlast the juggernaut.  Would love to see or be shown a better option.", 'Yeah.  For this season, there’s no point in trying to negotiate something: the risk is too high for you on a fall turn.  But maybe once you’re turtled up and we’re looking at a slightly safer spring move, we can discuss some way to slingshot me past you', 'Absolutely.', 'And sorry for slow reply - been traveling', "No worries - we're on an extended clock right now.", 'tap-tap', 'Whassup?', 'Making sure the mic was working now', 'Heh indeed it is!']

messages: ["Hi Italy, hope you're doing well. I'll be figuring out the situation north of me for the beginning stages so I hope we can keep Pie and Lyo/Wes/Tys  dmz'd if that's ok with you?", 'Hope you are around. Would be good to chat at least briefly 🙂', 'Had some technical issues, but the trains are running on time now.', 'Great, what do you think of my proposal?', "Shoot, I was running through the messages so fast I forgot about your proposal by the time I responded.  Sounds like you might have enough on your hands without me annoying you in sensitive spaces, so I'm happy to honor such a DMZ", "Thanks, let's have a good game!", "Oh, gdi.  Now I have to tell a truth that sounds like the most cliched lie in the game: my order update didn't take, I wasn't intending to go to Piedmont.  Yes, I know it sounds ridiculous, but in this case true.", "Good news is that with your opinion this is more of an opportunity than a disaster (I'd still rather be in Tyrolia where I'm *supposed* to be) - I can bounce you in Mars to help keep you in Burgundy, or if you tell me to eff off, I can move back up to Tyrolia", 'Yes, please, go off on adventures elsewhere ...', 'Will do!', 'What plans do you have for Boh? I can maybe support you into Mun if that is likely to succeed', "As awesome as that sounds, I have an Austrian problem to deal with first.  Hopefully diplomatically, we'll see", 'Do you need help? I could build a fleet in Mar, maybe', "You probably have other priorities to attend to, but if can get in position I'm happy to do anything that frustrates Austria", "If you can help a push into Munich, then that's one less flank for you to worry about", "How are you holding up? It looks bad initially, but Austria will need to disband a lot in Fall because of Turkey's stab. Not sure how you will come out of it though. Do you need help in fending off Turkey?", "Oh, I'm fine, and highly amused\nI wouldn't mind being the mover into Munich, though.", "I don't think I'm going for munich this turn but you can give it a shot", "Just as well I didn't see this before the turn processed.", 'I was thinking the same thing...', 'Austria dead in one turn, impressive', "Poor guy - I was really upset we couldn't come to any sort of agreement or arrangement.", "So, now that Turkey is going to have 4 fleets in the Mediterranean, what's in the future?", "I doubt they're just going to sit there and let us be.", 'War, my friend.  War is in our future.  The faster you can get your fleets into play, the better it will go for us', "Ok. I'll try to get there.", "I'm also moving Mar to Pie. Hope that's ok with you.", 'It is what it is.  We needs do what we must', "I'm sure you expect that I'm coming to attack you and, indeed, Turkey is trying to set me up against you. But the way I look at it is that if we were to split your CP, Turkey would still win. I can't let that happen", 'Now you can retreat to Tun and get a CP', 'What, pray tell, does CP stand for?', "Oh, sorry it's a supply center. I think mixed lingo there", 'I figured you meant support center, I was just curious which language had the abbreviation as CP. 😃', 'Probably some strategy game', "I'm hoping to get to Mun this round. if you could support Ruh into Mun that would be appreciated. I can support Tyr in turn", 'Alternatively, pressure R somehow to take away support from Mun.', 'We should also come up with a strategy for the mediterranean', 'I figure T is going to Very annoying with that fleet, threatening my supply or supporting a push into Italy. Not quite sure yet how to resolve that.', 'Good morning', "Just need to put pressure on R and T, and try to outlast the juggernaut.  At least, that's my view 🙂"]

messages: ['Hello Austria! I just want to open up communications, since the two of us will be working together for most of the game.', "Indeed! What's your read on the west thus far?", "I haven't heard back from anyone else yet, so I'm assuming it's going to develop the normal way (me and France fighting in the west while you and Russia fight in the east). It's critical for us to work together so we aren't steamrolled by either France-England or Russia-Turkey, so do you want to agree to an alliance right off the bat?", 'Absolutely. One of my favorite things about this game is that it can reflect real life history in certain grander strategic considerations, one of which is that, just as would have been the case, neither Germany nor Austria benefits from an antagonistic relationship.', "So given the first move, I think the two of us are in a relatively strong position. Turkey seems to be focusing more on Russia than you, and England and France are fighting. Are you going to focus more on Russia or Turkey first? I could try and stop Russia from taking Scandinavia unopposed, but I'd need assurance first that you're going to put pressure on them from the south since a move like Warsaw --> Silesia would screw both of us.", "I'm feeling pretty solid about working with Turkey, so Russia is the target for now.", "So it seems like Italy's turned on us. I can support Vienna --> Tyrolia next move if you want", "I'm down. Turkey and I will be able to crack Ionian, and Italy will fall hard."]
sender_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True]

messages: ['Hey Germany! How’s it going? Looking forward to a fun game!', "Hello! I'm looking forward to a fun game as well. I usually see good things happen when Russia and Germany work together, so I hope we can both help each other in our initial plans. I'm assuming you're gonna try and attack Scandinavia first? Let me know your thoughts, and I look forward to us working well together", 'Hi Germany - sorry I’m behind the eightball here - got swamped with work', 'But that seems to have worked out well for you so I’m sure you’re not too upset lol', "To be honest I was expecting to bounce in Sweden 😅 . From what I've heard England is gonna move Norway --> St. Petersburg this Spring, just thought I'd let you know.", 'Haha word']
sender_labels: [True, False, True, True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True, True, 'NOANNOTATION', True]

messages: ["How's it going Germany just wanted to reach out and get your thoughts on the game?", "Hello. I don't have much to go off yet since no orders have been placed, but I'm hoping we can work together during this game. At least in my experience, Germany and Britain tend to work well together since we both have the threat of France, and I would be willing to fend them off while you attack the Russians up north. Let me know your thoughts", "I like to work with people so I'm open to that plan. I figured I would probably stalemate with Russia for a while while they figured out what was happening down south.", "It feels like years since we've talked. I've noticed russia hasn't really made any moves into the north and wanted to know if we could amicably split up the northern territories?", 'I agree, it seems like Russia is undefended in St. Petersburg. If you let me keep Sweden you can have whatever other centres you want in Russia.', "Alright that's seems reasonable."]
sender_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True, True, False, 'NOANNOTATION']

messages: ['Hello Turkey! Just opening up communication', 'Comms channel authenticated. Ready to receive transmissions!', 'Wait, so why are you attacking both France and England at the same time?  That seems... dangerous?', "I wasn't attacking them, I had non-aggression with them and I had assumed they would've been preoccupied with Russia at least for a few years. I think I can kick out their army in Holland, and from there I guess we'll see what happens.", '"non-aggression" doesn\'t exist in this game, in my experience.  You either have allies who you work with to divide spoils, or you have people fighting you or about to.', "Moving Kie-Hel is a clear act of aggression against England.  Which is fine since they attacked you at the same time, but if they hadn't, they certainly would now!", "I agree, I was mostly relying on the fact that England wouldn't attack France, Russia, AND me at the same time.", "We'll see how things play out", "England didn't - they *helped* Russia, and given they didn't move to ECH last season, they've clearly been resolving their issues with France.  I would assume they are talking a lot at this point.", "They're taken ECH now, and even if the support into Sweden proves Russia and England have an alliance there isn't much they can do. I agree that I'm in a bit of a tight spot, but I still have full confidence, especially with you and Austria taking on Russia and Italy so effectively.", "I just gave Russia back their supply center, so they're actually building 2 units now, fyi...", 'Shit...', "What you need is an ally you can count on, or you'll be going down quickly unless the board changes significantly.  Maybe start talking to France?", 'already have been', 'Heh, talking while punching hard into Bur makes it hard to come up with a good alliance plan...', 'Hey there.  Who do you hate most?  Russia, France, or England?', "Tbh, they all played well. I'm not mad, it was mostly me who fucked up anyways"]
sender_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, True]

messages: ['Hello France! Just opening up communication. Hope we have a good game together', "Hi Germany, good to talk to you. Were you hoping for particular command centers in the low lands? I'm considering going for belgium", "Based on what I've heard so far (I have a suspicion England might try for either Holland or Belgium). I'm gonna go for a pretty conservative start (Kiel --> Denmark, Berlin --> Kiel, Munich Hold). Do you want to agree that I take Holland and you take Belgium, then see where we go from there?", "I think that's fine with me.", "I'm considering playing fairly aggressive against England and cutting them off at the pass in 1901, your support for that would be very helpful.", "Sure, a strong England is always a threat to me, so I'd be happy to help annoy them in the North Sea/Scandinavia", "Ok, let's see how things play out and I'll be in touch if I need help", "It's unfortunate you decided to move this way because now it gets more difficult to stop England", "I agree, there's a good chance England can take Belgium this fall, but I'm also still confident in my position. I'm sorry about your position, that's mostly bad luck.", 'You had assured me Munich would hold but then I find out it moves to Bur instead.', "It wouldn't have changed the final position anyway since you supported with Marseille.", "I would've liked to work together and at least take out england quickly", 'But I see you have other plans', "So, given the moves of England this Fall, it seems clear that they're attacking both of us. I know I've been... aggressive to you in the past, and I know that chances are you won't believe me or agree to work with me, but if you hear me out we both can gain from this (and utterly destroy England in the process). I'll retreat from Burgundy this Spring, and I'll agree to not invade any more territories of yours until all of England is destroyed. I'm assuming you're going to build a fleet in Brest, and if you do so and move Bre --> Eng in the spring it would cut any support that fleet could provide and I can kick England out of the North Sea. From there I can help support you in to the English Channel or we could work to convoy an army into the British Isles in the next few years. I hope you consider.", 'I am considering it. England in the channel was not great']
sender_labels: [True, True, False, True, False, False, True, True, True, True, True, False, True, True, False]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True, False, True, True, True, True, True, True, True, False, True, True, True]

messages: ['Hey Austria! How’s it going? Looking forward to a fun game!', 'As am I! What direction are you inclined to go? Are you willing to DMZ Galicia?', "Well, I suppose it's probably a mite hypocritical of me to get angry about the Galicia bounce, but, since you didn't confirm a DMZ, I felt like I had to protect it. Now that we've seen some tangible move data, what are you thinking?", 'I’m down to work together! I got swamped at work yesterday (I work in politics lol) and this slipped my mind. Won’t happen again', 'All good. :)', 'What’s up Austria?', 'Feeling good, I think things are going well.']
sender_labels: [True, True, True, True, True, True, True]

messages: ["How's it going Austria, just wanted to say hello.", "Doing alright. Haven't heard from many folks yet, so I don't have any concrete plans yet", "Yeah, I've only heard from you and Russia so far. But to be fair I only just reached out to anyone."]
sender_labels: [True, True, True]
receiver_labels: [True, True, True]

messages: ['A/T move fast and break things?  I’m fleets you’re armies, kill Russia quick, let Italy fart around a few years then carve them up too? Whaddya say?', "Solid plan. I'm in.", "Cool.  Let's see how our neighbors start talking to see how easiest to proceed (i.e if I need to gun right after Russia out of the gate [and hence watching my back against an early agressive Italy], or if I can slip fleets out into the med super early, because we think Russia might not be as much of an early concern, etc...)", 'This is looking quite promising! I look forward to a productive alliance.', 'I have to play some guessing games with Russia - I covered my butt with Arm, but I was hoping I wouldn’t lose Bla.  But you and I are good, and I’m in position to go “mostly fleets” and you my army-heavy ally.  What do you think about Italy?', "Well, I got him to go to Piedmont, which I didn't expect to work, and having bounced Russia out of Galicia, none of my centers are under threat, so even if Italy gets cute, I'm covering Trieste.", "Italy decided to break with me, but, you and I will be able to crack Ionian, so, we'll make him regret it, eh?", "Oh wow, they sure did try to sucker-punch you!  I'm game to go after them, sure, but if Russia starts actually ordering instead of NMR, taking on both of them will be doable, but... slow, right?  Maybe we convince Russia to go deal with their northern front (since there is an E/G clearly)?", 'True, if Russia pulls BLA then we can definitely leave them alone for a while.', 'Yep.  Let them keep War/Mos warm for us for a while, and keep those juicy dots out of English hands. 😉', 'Russia is willing to focus north, holding England back, so we can leave them alone for a while and take out Italy.  Do you want me to support you into Ion, or do you want my unit to be the mover?  We’ll probably bounce in spring so it won’t matter, but fall we’ll succeed so we should decide who is the mover.', "I'll do the moving.", "sounds good.  You'll have one support in Spring, and then when that doesn't work, two in the fall.", 'Double support of Gre-Ion, right?', "That's what I understand the plan to be, yep!", 'Ok, got you into Ion.  Are you attempting to guess a convoy (Nap/Apu?) and want me to support the fleet, or can I do a supported attack on Ion while you move your fleet forward (to Tun/Tys/Nap/Adr)?  We should definitely move forward, but we need to coordinate how to do it.', "BTW: I gave Russia Sev back so they could build against Germany, who was getting way too big. They're building a northern fleet (absolutely no threat to either of us), and probably either Moscow or Warsaw, depending on if going after Scandanavia or towards Berlin.  Just fyi.", 'And we work to split Italy between the two of us, right?  Tri/Rom for you, Nap/Tun for me?', 'All sounds good to me. My initial train of thought is, you should do a supported attack on Ionian, while I send my fleet to Apulia. That cuts any chance of that fleet supporting Venice, and guarantees I get in to Venice. How does that sound to you?', "That sounds good, sure.  If Apu-Nap happens, then you're *in* Apu, which is fine, as it can support follow-on movements to Venice as well.", '(follow-on meaning when your army in Venice continues on to Rome)', 'If I succeed in pushing you forward out if Ion,   and you’re in Apu and Italy is in Nap, we can actually convoy to Nap with support from Apu unless Tun goes to Tys, but in that case Tunis would be open.  Would you want Gre to be the convoy, or could I convoy from Bul?', "I'd be down for you convoying.", "excellent, it's a plan!", 'Sigh. We coulda been so good together.', 'Yeah I know.  I got greedy.  :\\', 'I mean, nothing is set in stone yet. You can take it back.', 'It’s true - Bud back to Rum and Ser on to Alb could position for more forward convoys without needing the rear fleet...', 'Exactly! My moves will be the same either way, but seeing you do that would be very encouraging.', 'Of course if I got stabbed by Russia for Rum at the same time, it would instead stab you, as I’d just bounce out of Rum and get stuck in Bud!  But I’m sure that’s a risk you’d be willing to take.', 'I’ll be honest I have to ponder that.  It’s tempting because Italy wouldn’t expect it at all, and would probably move assuming help from me, which would wreck them further', "Exactly. It'd definitely throw a wrench in what the Italian expects.", 'More than expects: they’re already explicitly asking for Ser-Tri to cut that support']

messages:
['Hey England! How’s it going? Looking forward to a fun game!', 'Doing well hope everything is going well on your front.', 'What are your plans in the north? If we butt heads too much germany might swoop in and get free territory.', 'Want to figure something out so Germany doesnt take the territory we deserve?', 'Sure!', "What are you thinking? I could possibly support you into swe if you'll later support me into Den?", 'You there?', "Germany is trying to play us both. I'm sure they said something about me attacking you, which I did per their request in exchange for a different territory. They have completely gone against what they said to me, which I kind of expected but figured i would take a chance on. I would like to work with you because Germany is about to run away with this game if we don't take some stuff in the north.", 'Yikes', 'Yeah I’m down to help!!', "I'm assuming you're going for swe right? I can support you in.", 'Assuming germany even moves back', 'Yeah let’s do it!', 'Thanks!', 'Hey what’s up england!', "Nothing much just trying to get rid of germany after all their meddling. If you can refrain from going after Norway I'd be willing to help you with Den.", 'I’m down!', "Or I could give norway if you support me into Den if that's more to your liking.", 'That might be cleaner if that’s cool with you', 'Then you can support me in the mainland', 'My army in Pru is gonna hit ber', 'Here’s my moveset atm:
F BAR - Nwy 
A Gal - Vie
A Pru - Ber
F Swe S NTH - Den
A Ukr - War', "If you support my move from NWY into Den then I'll leave NWY open for you to grab.", 'Oh gotcha convoy', 'Done', 'Perfect thanks.', 'Updated 
F Swe S Nwy - Den', 'You got it dude', 'Hey England how’s it going?', 'Just getting wrecked, the usual.', 'Hahaha', 'You want to hold off for a sec so I can take out france?', 'Perhaps.', "Well I can't really stop you otherwise so it's up to you.", 'Hahahah fair enough', 'Have you heard much from Turkey?', 'Yeah they want me to hold you off while you they get rid of france. They dont want you getting all my stuff.']

messages:
['Is the Juggernaut boring? No, I say - it’s simply *retro*!  When executed with panache, they can even be elegant! I thought it would be so fun to have a nice game where we work together and score a two way victory.', 'It’ll still probably end up that way, frankly.   Just seeing England roll over like a sick jellyfish and France continue to hold me off while crumbling to you... I figured worst case scenario: you still kill the entire west, I rule the east.  You realize you’re *still* closer to Gibraltar than I am!  So yeah, I didn’t think you were *planning* to screw me, I just looked at the map and saw: what if England and France just *gave him* the win?  Can’t I just cover my ass so even if he grows by 4 next year, I’m still ok?  And seriously: watch how it goes: even with this move, there is nothing I or they can do to stop you from crushing that whole side of the board.  And in 3 full game years? They’ll *still* both be dead!', 'Yeah I guess, I mean we’ll played I suppose', 'But I am not trying to blow you some lame line: do what you gotta do!  But it the map doesn’t change: you already have complete domination over the west on your own, and I am not jealous- you did awesome.  I’m just trying to play a little catch up, since France opted to just slow me down and let you have England, instead of take them out and risk me catching the unawares.  Totally in their right, of course.', 'Yeah for sure but if you felt that way you could have asked.', '“Could you please slow down killing them so brutally so I can catch up?”  That’d be some pretty sad shit!  If I deserved to be doing better, I’d have outplayed France’s tactics or convinced them to somehow be somewhere else.', 'But yeah I could have proposed “you west, me east?” and you probably would have set some conditions but been ok with it.  I’ve seen how you play.', 'Yeah for sure I would  have been happy and willing give you a few of my centers to keep parity', 'Yeah you have before.  We both have. I guess I figured it’d end up that way anyway, and “it’s easier to ask for forgiveness than permission”, as lame as that sounds.', 'I guess', 'So I’ll totally deserve it if I get stuck in a mere 3-way draw when I coulda cruised into a clean 50/50 split with a game long ally.  You can say I told you so, and it’ll be my own damn fault.']

['Hey France! How’s it going? Looking forward to a fun game!', 'Hi Russia, hope we can keep each other informed of relevant information, say on Germany and England, if convenient 🙂', 'I’m super down!', 'Looks like something went wrong for fall?', 'Yeah man - I was swamped with work', 'I work in politics so you can imagine it’s been a crazy week hahaha', 'You mean the vote counting thing? Yeah that seems to have blown up', 'Yeah nuts haha', 'We’ll see what happens', "Alright, so, I'm kind of tangled with Germany. England is my temporary friend. I think they also want to hit Germany.", "I think England may have seen Stp as a move of opportunity, I'm not sure, since if they had moved to Swe it would've been a lot better, honestly", 'I can work with you guys', "I think it's clear that it's just a matter of time before you overrun England's position. Would you mind divvying up the remains?", 'Hey France! Appreciate you not hitting me last year.  I could be down for something like that', 'What’s your relationship like with England? Until last turn I was under the impression you guys were allies', 'We were/are, yeah. But Englands position is not tenable. E made some mistakes when we were mopping up G and it just took too long.', 'Makes sense. Aside from me and turkey you’re clearly the strongest and it works for me to work with you so I can just focus on England', 'What are you thinking in terms of this season?', 'I wish my fleets were available', 'Ugh same', "I'm thinking of siding with E for another season and then going for a stab in Holland in Fall", 'Yeah that makes sense', 'I’d have to look at it again in the morning but I might be down to help you out', 'Clearly turkey and I are allies so I’m not tryna step on any toes', 'Fair enough', 'I’d be very interested in what moves england is planning on making', "I'll see if I can put a fleet in Mao to go for Lvp while you take the east side", 'Yeah that would be legit.', 'I’m down to support you into Holland', 'Fighting you over it would be a pain for both of us', 'Could you get me intel on England’s next moves?', "I'm reaching out but we'll see if they're still tuned in to the game", 'Gotcha wouldn’t be shocked if they check out', 'This study is so much fun', 'Like getting paid to play this game, what can beat that?', 'That is awesome, yeah. Though I wish I could play diplomacy in a short burst 😄', 'Turkey seems to be taking things very seriously', 'Yeah I feel like he’s hardcore', 'Maybe we can look at him after we build up strength by taking out england', "I've played Turkey a couple of times but never got Russia to ally with me. It's quite strong", "At the same time, I've never seen such an eagerness to cooperate either", "I'm guessing Turkey imposed DMZs on Vie/Bud etc?", 'It’s not overly formal', 'Mostly we had a common interest in taking out Austria', 'And I skipped a turn early on and needed an ally to survive', 'Ah yes I remember that', 'The Sev disband probably helped with the mutual trust 🙂', 'Absolutely', 'So do you want support into hol this turn or wait til fall?', 'What’s good France', 'If I remember correctly we were just starting to work together against england lol', "Yeah, I'll move out to Lvp now and see if we can push through the fleets", 'Awesome! If you build a fleet you can help me take the North Sea. Once we break England’s baby we’re chilling', "Cool, I'm moving into Eng. Any particular plans from there?", 'We can talk about how to divid it up. We definitely should make sure we both get builds. we’re good to pause aggression on our front on the continent?', 'Sounds good', "Do you have a will to team up on Turkey at this point? I can't stop T by myself", 'Maybe! I don’t know if we could take him at this point', 'Realignments are always possible 🙂', 'Yeah I agree', 'Clearly turkey stabbed me. If it’s not too late, I want to take you up on your offer to work together.', 'Let me know what you’re thinking. I’m super on board to work together.', 'Hello?', 'Hey, sorry was busy playing Civ with some friends 🙂', 'Lol nice!', 'How are you holding up with the craziness?', "Yeah it's a time sink", "I'm fine, just gotta keep social contacts going even though they're virtual", 'Absolutely!', 'But the board state is giving me a headache', 'Join the club', 'Has turkey reached out to you at all?', "I think, given our position we can't survive if we don't work together", '100%', "Like, I don't think you can protecct War,Mos & Sev by fall", "For me, I don't know about Spain & Por.", 'Nah. I think the only one of my original supply centers I can save is StP', 'I think we have to put England to bed quickly so we can turn all our sights on Turkey.', "Luckily it's somewhat independent", 'Though it seems likely turkey would reach out to E, perhaps', 'Yeah of course.', 'I haven’t spoke much with him since the early game.', 'At the end of the day we have to just survive three years.', 'Yeah he just wants to take you on', 'I don’t think he’ll be useful against England and I rather put one front to bed so we can focus on the real enemy', '*against Turkey', 'With a tightly coordainated strategy I think we can at least force a 3 way draw, perhaps even regain some ground.', 'It looks like you can get Lvp and Edi this turn.', 'Yup.', 'I could chase after Mao or go for Lon, what do you think?', 'I’m more worried about the fleet than the army', 'I think one rouge English fleet could be a hastle whereas the army is trapped on the mainland and will probably get disbanded anyway', 'I also think we need to go on the offensive in the balkans before he gets more builds', 'I can support Pie to Tyr which should break his line', "Yeah, I'll be withdrawing from Ruh to cover my CP from Mao then and potentially get through to italy", 'I’m hoping he stretches himself a little too thin taking my home centers and opens up Central Europe for us to dive in', 'Perfect. We can’t let him get out of the Mediterranean', 'As we move forward, once I start taking centers in the balkans I would be happy to return hol and other centers to keep you strong', 'Actually could you support mun to tyr?', 'That would be a faster way for me to deploy my armies away from you and get them at the front lines ASAP', "I'd be happy to, but I expect Pie to get attacked", "So don't count on it", 'From venice with support from Tyr.', 'And Tus', 'Gotcha that doesn’t shock me.', 'I’m gonna support with Boh as well', 'Fair enough. Since you can't use builds atm anyway.", 'I feel like I need all my fleets in the Mediterranean so it must be an army', 'Totally happy to do any trade that works best for our alliance', 'I’m so excited that you broke through his line in the balkans', 'That will be huge', 'Depending on how annying England plans to be, would you mind advancing to the english channel so you can support me in kicking out an english fleet?', 'Yes', 'How do you see the situation develop from Tyr?', "We can pressure both War and Vie but that doesn't guarantee success as long as Mos is there", 'True', 'Not sure. My thinking would be to get some guys behind his lines and force him to push back. I agree that Vie and War should be the main targets.', 'He could bounce himself over Ven and prevent any such way in.', 'oh no. But we need to pressure War', 'in the next turn, if we live.', 'Turkey is smart he’ll lock it up.', 'Okay this might work', 'Tyr hits Pie', 'Spain hits lyo', 'Braking the support wherever it comes from', 'Saving Mar', 'Then Portugal defends Spain', 'That should keep us alive.', 'Actually, A Tyr S Mar - Pie could work but not tyr attacking Pie directly', 'F MAO S Por - Spa/sc

A Mar - Pie

A Tyr S Mar - Pie', 'wait.. no', 'Yeah no haha', 'You’ll def lose it then', 'I think my plan will work', 'why does Tyr attack Pie? Even though that's kinda useless", 'So whoever it is we hit them garunteeing we brake the support either way', 'But then Mun can move up', 'F MAO S Por - Spa/sc

I’m about to call it a night.', 'Yea, but my point still stands that we need a center somewhere to compensate', 'How do we get one?', 'Perhaps War', 'Yeah that’s our best shot. You want me to throw everything I have at it?', "You'd probably need an army in Stp to do it.", 'Yup :/', 'Hey anything we need to go over before adjudication?', "don't think so", 'Unless you want some advice on your own moves', 'Is there anything you would change?', 'F BAR - NWG

messages: ['Hello Turkey, just wanted to say hello and hope we have a fun game!', 'How dare you!  I declare war!', 'Shit.  Was I supposed to click “I’m lying” or “I’m telling the truth” for sarcasm?  This is hard! 😉', 'So these brave young Englishmen begin their march across the continent to wage war on a country or possibly a bird?', 'good question on the sarcasm, may throw of the numbers at the end', 'I’m going to go with “am I intending to deceive” as the spirit of the law', 'I did the same', 'Thankfully they explicitly mention it’s ok to have the infamous “It was true when I said it!” excuse', "maybe they've run into this issue previously", 'Among diplomacy players? Never.', "Hey are you doing anything with russia? I've tried reaching out to them and they haven't responded back to me so I'm assuming they're plotting something.", 'Well they definitely are plotting lots of things.  I covered myself with Arm, but them taking Bla will require some guesswork on my part.  Hopefully I can convince them to just take Rum with the fleet...', "Alright, them not responding to me and pushing north makes me think they don't really have any desire to work with me. Just figured I'd talk to you to see if we could coordinate so russia isn't able to easily push both fronts.", 'How did they push north?  3 units went south, the only northern move they did is StP-GoB.', 'From what I can tell, Russia was worried that Austria and I were ganging up on them (at least that’s what Austria tells me, and the excuse Russia gave for both War-Gal and Sev-Bla).  So I’m game to try and out guess them with you, but I think Russia is looking for an ally anywhere.  If you offered an alliance with them (real or fake) they would probably take it.  For example if you offered to convoy to Den while they drop into Bal, they’d probably do that, setting off an R/G war (not sure if you want that, but you could).', 'Seems like you and Germany are already teaming up on France, so you can probably keep Russia contained in the north without too much effort, right?', "I'm not teaming on France. Also I assumed russia was going to go for Norway so I'm a bit confused with their plan as they haven't talked to me other than saying hello.", 'StP(sc) can’t move to Nwy - it’s on the wrong coast as a fleet.', "I mean when they were in Stp, and then they didn't try to go got Swe at all.", 'StP doesn’t touch Sweden: the northern Russian fleet can never bother England in the first few years of the game: its moves are almost always StP(sc) - GoB, then GoB-Swe.  The only time England ever has to worry about Russia in 1901 is if they send A Mos-StP, because *that* unit *can* threaten Nwy.', 'Maybe we’re misunderstanding each other?', "Yeah I think we are, I was talking about over multiple turns. It's just weird how russia isn't making any moves for depots in the north and seems to be letting germany just have at it.", "Russia didn't move because they lost track of time, it wasn't intentional, I'm sure.  I haven't heard from them since the Spring moves.", "Okay, I wasn't sure if had been some mind gaming or what happened.", 'No, they totally screwed their position by not moving - look in the south!', "Yeah, that's why I wasnt sure if they were just playing really passive to try some trick. But it's pretty obvious now looking at it.", 'So it looks like while you worked something out with Russia, to carve Germany up, you’re now reorienting against them.  You want to coordinate anything with me, or am I “the enemy”? 🙂', "I'm completely fine coordinating, what are you thinking?", 'Well both of us have only two main competitors left: France and Russia. If we each take on one while the other goes after the other, we’ll kinda split the board up but it’ll be slow.  If we pick the same enemy, it’ll go faster, but we’ll have to leave ourselves a little undefended in the opposite side.  I go after Russia, most likely France grows big in the Med.  You go after France, Russia is breathing down your neck.  That’s my main concern: how do I go after Russia if I know France will quickly be taking control of Italy?  Can we somehow keep France tied down so we’re free to mostly focus on Russia?', 'Wow, did France actually stab you? In this position?!?  Doesn’t he know you can throw your remaining strength into making sure he dies, to spite the stab?  Maybe she thinks there is not enough time in the game for me and Russia to eliminate him?', 'Is France spinning you some tale about how they took Holland to build fleets to hold me back?', "No, they haven't responded", "I've been backstabbred so I shall in turn backstabbr.", "I can ask Russia if they will lay off off you for a couple of seasons so you can throw your units against France.  I'm sure he'll attack you eventually, but I could probably get you a two season head start?", "Yeah, I get the feeling I'm not going to survive much longer anyway. But it would be nice to get back at france for their betrayal.", 'I’m attacking France with all my strength. If you send Nth-Ech you’ll block Bre-Ech, and if you also do Nwg-Nao and Edi-Nwg you can maybe take France down with you!', "please please please build an army at home to defend for a few more seasons?  I'm attacking France and will help you exact your revenge on them, just don't give all your centers to Russia? 🙂", "If I can get into Spain, I will support you to hold in Portugal until the end of 1910 so that if we do it right, France gets eliminated for stabbing you, and you survive with that center plus whatever you can hold in Britain (which I can't help either way with)", "That was my plan, if I can take our france I'll die in peace", 'I’ll of course be glad to help enact the killing France part of that plan!', 'so Russia is deciding to kill you to save his ass.  Can you bring Lon-Eng to help me crush them both?', 'Wal-Lon to watch your back at the same time.', "That's was my thoughts.", "France will probably crush Portugal if I don't help now.  And you perhaps getting to convoy Wal-Bre is my only chance at cracking Mar or Spa"]

messages:
['Howdy France, just wanted to reach out and see what your thoughts on the game were.', "Hey England, I was wondering how you would want to align yourself, assuming it's not against me, how far would you go to attack G or will you go with a northern opening against R?", "I'm thinking of a defensive strategy to start just to see how things shake up, I'm considering  an arctic expedition though.", 'I see, well I was hoping to lure germany in a bit and then turn the table on them with you', 'I would to free up my fleet to MAO so that I can respond to Italian aggression but your move to the channel has me worried. Do you plan to take norway?', 'Yeah, I plan on taking Norway and wanted my fleet already in the water to move wherever needed. I figured at some point we would negotiate who could go for bel or hol while you get the rest of the iberian peninsula.', 'Yeah, I was hoping to get a foothold in Bel. From there I could support e.g. your new build into Hol.', 'There seems to be some sort of central non aggression pact going based on their movements.', "Since G decided to stab me, I'm inclined to get back at them", 'I think we need to worry about germany getting alot of territory early.', "Yeah, Russia is going south, same for Austria. G has a free playing field. I don't think we can stop 2 builds for G either", "I'll probably reach out to russia and see if we can stop them from getting too crazy in the north.", 'afk for a bit', 'I will also be on and off so might responses may be delayed today and tomorrow.', 'So what do you want to do with the channel? Mutual bounce?', "So that it looks like we're going for each other?", "Let's see. We should plan out 1902 because after that G basically should have completed their Atlantikwall and we can't get you in to help me any more", "I need to see what I does. I'm hoping I changes their mind about attacking Mar because that's not so easy.", "I agree, they're benefiting a lot from neither of us having moved into that spot.", 'If that goes well, I should have an army in Bel by fall 1902 or ready to support', "I've got my fleet going for eng.", "Great. Let's see how things shake out", 'Did you reach some agreement with Russia?', "No, they still haven't responded to me. I'm not sure why they moved the way they did unless they're not trying to piss of Germany.", 'How do you feel about next year moving your fleet into pic and I move mine into the eng and one of us can support the other into Bel?', 'I could also go for Den and move my fleet into Nth to support you as well.', "I think R just didn't submit orders", "I'm cool trying to support you into Bel. I'm thinking about how to move so that G gets removed from Bur while also being able to support an attack on Bel", 'I think maybe moving my fleet to Mao so that I can take Portugal in fall and you can take Eng to support an attack on Bel could be an option?', "I'm fine with that plan. I finally got russia to respond so hopefully we'll be able to work together to stop Germany from the top and I can help you push them back as well.", 'Maybe we can convince Austria to push from the other side to put pressure on all sides?', "Maybe but I'd think it unlikely", 'Yeah, might be to early for them to start backstabbring', "Since Italy tried for Tri, that's gonna be their focus. And R is no longer AFK so hopefully that will help", 'As in, keep A busy', 'Instead of focusing on Bel, we could put pressure on Hol & Den if you move to Hel? What do you think?', "I was trying to convoy my army into den because I'm assuming germany is going to try to move their fleet there. But I suppose we'll have two more turns to get them out if I just go hel.", "Russia is back, but they're still really bad about responding.", 'What would you achieve by convoying to Den?', 'My army in edi to stop Germany from taking it.', 'btw, you can go A Nwy-Stp, see if R is paying attention haha', 'Just the threat of that may force R to defend and will allow A Nwy-Swe', 'Then in Fall you have another support for attack on Den', 'Might have to since they are responding at all.', "There's a good chance G is sweettalking them and offering Swe and an alliance", "I suppose that's always a possibility", "Germany responded back to a message I sent a while ago telling me I can have at Russia if I let them keep swe. So I'm going to guess they're probably saying something similar to russia.", 'Are you okay with me moving my fleet into Eng?', "Russia is basically a vassal state of Germany as far as I can tell. Maybe you can try to talk some sense into them? I'm going to plan on moving my fleet into Eng this round, and see how I can support you from there.", "Hey, did you get my messages? I'm not sure if they got through", "No I didn't get any since you talking about germany sweet talking.", 'Reposting:
Sure, I had expected you to move it to Eng in Spring tbh
Now, without Eng to support, it will be hard to take Bel if G makes the right moves.', "I figured since you hadn't said anything you were not thrilled with the idea.  We can always blame our diplomacy overseer for anything going poorly.", "Have you tried talking to russia? I'm wondering if only you had issues sending me messages or if it was a larger issue?", "I have, but I don't think there were issues with the server. They were just busy IRL", "If you didn't have the emoji show up on your messages or didn't click either 👍 or 👎 , just assume it didn't send", 'The more I look at the board the more likely it seems T & R are biding their time for R to rebuild and then ally up', 'Not that it matters for us currently, we would still have to crush G asap to get the cp we need to defend against that', "So what's next? Will you support me into Bel?", "Yeah I think they're probably going to working together as well. Yeah I'll support you in.", 'After I push G out of Bur, I can push for Mun while you go for Kie or Den', 'Sounds like a solid plan to me', 'Sounds like a solid plan to me', "Alright, so I'll try to get Bel this turn, can I get your support for that?", "Based on Russia's fleet I think I'm going to be having some trouble in the north soon.", 'Yeah I saw that', 'Thanks for the assist by the way', 'Turkey and Russia almost definitely teamed up', "Definitely working together. What's your plan this season? Hold or push further? I'm possibly getting backstabbred by russia and making a push for Den.", "I think Den is good. G will probably disband fleets. You can also just go Nwy-Stp on retreat if you're afraid of the stab there...
I'll move the line up to munich for a push next year. You can take Kie with my support or Den with your fleet, and I take Mun after.", "There's a small chance you can just do A Hol-Kie, since G needs to cover Ber from R", 'Actually, if you could do that, that would guarantee I can move into the Ruhrgebiet', 'I can give it a shot', 'Are you moving Bel? If not could you support, hol in case Germany tries a push there?.', 'I was thinking of using bel to support a move into Ruh', 'Can you support A Bur-Ruh? Then I can support a hold in Hol.', 'Yes, I just updated to support bur into ruh', 'Ok. Will update.', 'I negotiated with russia not realizing they were going to easily walk into Austria and Germany. I may have thrown this game, my bad.', 'Yeah, R & T position is very strong now.', "Could you move Eng out to NTH? Or elsewhere? I'm moving Bre to Mao and Mao to Wes", "Yeah, I'm moving the up to hopefully contest russia.", 'Can you support me moving Nth into Hol? And support Kie if possible? Once I get Hol I think I should be pretty good to hold off Russia from the north.', "I can support Hol but I'm using Ruh to push into Mun, or at least prevent R from doing so.", 'support a push into Hol', "Okay. Also turkey reached out to me about attacking russia together, but they wanted to know how I would stop you from taking over the Med. Are you fine with me going for one of your suppy points to make it look like we're fighting?", "After Italy is finished I mean, we can coordinate it so that it just looks like I'm going for it but you can defend it.", 'Just something for the future.', "Right, it's possible but there are no convincing moves available at the time so really you could say that you're not in a good position for a stab", 'Yeah, I think they want something later on', "Hey, it would've been much more helpful if you had used Kie to attack Ber. Now R has an extra CP for free :/ Should've spotted that as well.", 'Imo, if you are doing a hold it needs to be with good reason', "and Den couldn't have been pushed out anyway (you could've also tried moving to Swe, just in case.", 'I was expecting russia to make an attack to be honest.', 'You making a push on Mun this turn?', "Because I get the feeling I'm about to get wrecked from the north and my best bet is to push through middle with you and cut Russia in half.", 'Yes, your support would be appreciated.', "I'm moving in with Ruh", 'Done, got me just in time', 'Thanks!', 'You have any thoughts on moving forward?', 'I figure trying to push russia out from the middle while I go from the top? I can try to support you into Mun, but I will probably lose Kie.', "I think it's too late for Mun now", 'Bah, adjucation at noon hmm', 'Holland is safe for now but R has some crazy navy built up', 'Do you have something I can assist with?', 'Just hitting russia at mun or kie to put some pressure on fhem.', 'Et tu France?']

messages: ['Dear France, I have come up with a masterful strategy for world domination, and  while I can’t give you all of the details (for obvious reasons), suffice to say, it involves killing you *last*!  So whatever I can do to keep you strong and healthy so there is still a France to kill (or, heaven forbid, be killied by?!?), I’m at your service!', '(Knowing whether to mark that as “truth” or “a lie” was tricky, when it should clearly be labeled “wishful thinking”, y’know?)', 'I must say, that was quite a mouthful to rate yeah.', "Yeah, I'm a bit of a chatty Cathy.  You'll either get used to it, or convince all my neighbors to kill me to shut me up. ;P", 'I hope you do well, I have a sweet spot for Turkey', 'Well then we must both hope that Italy does *poorly*, in which case both of our hopes for each other doing well will be increased. 🙂', "Not always... but usually.  It's probably been a while since I've been on a board where F, I, and T all did well.", "I'm not even sure that is possible. Maybe in an extremely concerted effort.", 'But as it turns out, that would be fine with me in this case.', 'In my neck of the woods, we call it "Care-bear" play. 🙂', "Speaking of Italy - they're the one I haven't heard from yet.  You?", 'Nothing yet.', 'Could be talking to A a lot or just afk for now', "Nobody I've talked to has heard from them, so I'm guessing the latter.", 'unless everyone is screwing with me already, which would be typical. 😛', 'I considered it.', 'Yeah, it\'d be much more fun for all of y\'all to say, "Oh yeah, jeez, Italy just blabbers on and on!  Oh, you haven\'t heard from them?  How strange..."', "It's fun but I want you to do well so no incentive for me to lie to you", "Rockin'. Then lemme know when you *do* hear from them, and it'll let me know whether that happened before, or *after* they talked to me. 🙂", "(and I'll give you the same info, natch)", 'Sure, would be nice for me to know if they are back', 'Nice defense over there.  It’s a fun start for France when you see moves to Eng, Bur, *and* Mar!  But even more fun when they are parried off 🙂', 'You have some... not fun guessing games for the fall though. I wish you luck in that!', "Did Russia stab you in Bla? What's your feeling for alliances?", 'Looks like Italy and A are friends maybe?', 'Russia told me they wouldn’t go.  I told them I wouldn’t go, but said I’d cover my ass.  Looks like I told they truth and they didn’t, but it’s not irreparable, at present.', 'I/A are friendly-ish.  The Rom-Ven means Austria will be covering Tri in fall.', 'Clearly E/G/I coordinated spring', 'I am ok with Austria.  I’ve actually done everything I said to everyone I’d do. Fat lot of good that’ll do me', "I believe what you're saying but I'm hoping they will see their initial alliances are no longer in their best interest 🙂", "it's hard to convince people though", 'If I go with A against R, it wouldn’t help you unfortunately: A shows no interest in anti-Italian early moves (which is sensible, if not ideal for you)', "That's fine, I just kinda need to know how eveyone aligns with G", 'because it looks like an amazing game for them from spring', 'I’m trying to convince England that it would be super fun to coordinate the “convoy-Den” + GoB-Bal move', 'But I don’t get the impression they’re that creative', 'GoB? You mean let G get Swe while convoying into Den?', 'Maybe you should play hardball with Italy: “lay off me and if you’re my only neighbor who didn’t attack me, and I go down, I’ll give you my dots to spite them.  Attack me with them, and you’ll get Mar and nothing more ever, I’ll make sure of it!”', 'Yes that’s what I mean.', 'I love risky plays like that. Once got Sev in 1901, that was fun', 'Hah nice!', 'Tbf, Italy has a great position to attack Austria', 'Oh I love the Pie-Trl + Ven-Tri + build A ven combo, it’s great if you can get those all to work in fall', 'Just need some help from Russia, get them to tell Austria they feel they really *have to* go to Gal again, and they’re happy to bounce, but they simply can’t risk holding in fall...', 'Does a bounce from War help that much?', 'It’s irrelevant now, since Italy *did* attack Austria. Unfortunately for you: your position would be much better had Italy attempted Mar! 😦', 'Yeah, I had considered it but I had to cover my bases', 'Yep understood', "Tricky situation... E/G finally fighting, and you lose Bur, but you really can't function with just one fleet, right?", "But luckily for you, Germany doesn't seem to understand this game is about negotiation and alliances.  Do you think you can count on England to actually work with you?", "I'm not sure but we share a common enemy", 'You know you could flip sides on the I/A axis and get half of the balkans probably right?', 'Nor do I want my right flank to succumb to austria', 'Succumb too Austria, succumb to me, six of one, half dozen of another, no?    But yes, A/I war is as fantastic for me as E/G war is for you.', "I don't see what you're gaining from this long term by letting R build back up. They seem intent to not anger G. So what then? Austria or you", 'Russia just took Sweden from Germany, with English help.', 'That was a lost cause', 'I encouraged that alliance, helping break the E/G you and Russia were so keen to have broken up.  Now England and Russia are both mildly anti-German.', "Sweden was only a lost cause for Germany if they fought with England.  If they'd known how to be an alliance player, they'd have been offering to give centers to England to cement their alliance.  They didn't do that, and got stabbed for it.", 'I don\'t understand people who play this game like it was gunboat.  The game is called diplomacy for a reason: make friends, use those friends to kill everyone off who doesn\'t have friends, try and convince other people to stop being friends with your enemies, and eventually kill your friends before they kill you.  Forget "the board"... "the dots" - it\'s about *the people*', 'but yes, if I want to win, I have to stab a knife into someone.  Gotta break some eggs to make an omelette and all that.', "so from your perspective, you're worried about seeing Austria get too big, is that what I'm hearing?  Or Russia?  What worries you, now that E/G is probably not a thing, for the time being?", "I see your assitance with Austria but I wouldn't want that to go too far because Italy's current position is unstable", 'Yeah Italy is ready to get pretty wrecked, unless Austria  or I decide to stop working together', 'So you coming to prop Italy up, or get a piece for yourself?  We should talk, either way!', "Right, I'm moving into the Mediterranean to get a better position for either case", 'why did you not support Kie and cut Munich?', 'Adjucation happened before I could think things through', "bummer. I never really get a chance to turn on Russia and slow them down if they keep growing so fast I never have an easy chance to stab... I'm doing my best to keep up with them at this point!", "I'm happy to cooperate since they will be +3  on your supply now", "I'm not quite sure what they would do by now but stab you or defend against a stab given that they have England in the bag", "as long as you're not helping England, that's for sure!", "That's true but I prefer to win", 'Is that really likely on this board?', "I don't know but I'd love for us to work together to make sure we both have a shot", 'Tactically, on this board, England falls to Russia, and you can’t hold back my fleets without two fleet builds (but then you can’t hold Burgundy on land). If Russia stabs me before I stab them, they have a shot at 18 before 1910.  I could stab them but I have much a smaller chance at 18 in time. There is no way you can get that big unless you eat England alive from behind before they know what’s happening', "I don't really play with the deadline in mind. Kind of ruins it for me :p", "In any case, I'm not just gonna sit here and die a slow death.", 'Sure, so pick  direction which has a possible  good outcome: there are two powers  on the board  capable of totally overrunning your position, so the only option is to somehow play them against each other (by suggesting to one of the two that you’d intentionally make the other one win the game, for example, and be willing to follow through on it) or be willing to think outside the box and throw yourself fully at one power or the other in a last ditch attempt to get as big as you can in the time left.  This is a game of alliances - being willing to sacrifice your position for a chance at either winning or dying in the process is the only shot any of us have!', 'would you have time to be able to stab England if you had a build from Italy, and then we could get Russia to support you into Hol?  With two builds, you could perhaps quickly get to England and kill them fast enough to hold Russia back until I stabbed them in the east, and you worked to control the west?', "I will try to talk to Russia and see how it goes. I just don't know if I can get a piece of Italy without arousing suspicion. Tunesia?", "Tunis is now undefended, and yes, if you were to promise you'd use the build you got from that center to attack England, I'd be ok with you taking that - I'd focus on the two remaining Italian home centers I've got almost surrounded, and would also promise to stop hitting Marseille soo you could bring your Pie army back home to ensure Burgundy is still more safe in case Russia won't help you and keeps attacking Ruh to get to Bur.", "But if Russia is willing to work with you, then yeah, you could get two builds, and you'd be back in this game, as you'd be able to get to Lvp/Lon before Russia could.", "But if you don't feel comfortable with any of that, I'd understand.  You've gotta do what you feel safest doing.  Don't even feel like you need to tell me - I'll do the same either way: Italy has turtled-up pretty good, so it'll take most of my effort just too crack Rom+Nap.  You can ignore Tun or take it - your choice.", "Sounds good. I'll use the Tun build to shore up my defenses with a fleet from Bre.", 'Did you come to an arrangement with Russia which ended up feeling safe for you to try?  This game could get to a 12-12-10 three way draw if you can get into position to get Lvp and Lon with builds from Tun and Hol.  I *think* there enough seasons before fall 1910 to get there still...', 'we still playing this game? 🙂', 'Yeah I thought about that', "We'll see what happens with Russia...", "Yep.  I re-read my orders, and I'm crushing Rome and letting you have Tunis to build for the last few game years", 'Ok, so where do you need to see my units to give you the breathing room to eliminate England by the end of 1910, so we can have a 3-way draw, instead of 4-way?', 'If we can DMZ some area between italy and me then that would free up my fleets', 'You are in the more precarious position (although the game is time limited so the danger isn’t quite so great).  So you make a specific proposal and I’ll tell you if that is asking too much or is fine as long as you keep your end of the bargain.', 'If you left it up to me, I could say: I’ll park my fleets on Italian coasts and leave TyS empty, but keep Ion for defense', "I normally make very specific proposals, so there's no ambiguity: if you are keeping two fleets in the Med, to protect Tunis, then I can offer to park Tunis on the coast, and do Nap-Tys, Rom-Tys (self bounce) and Ion-Tun (to cut your support so you can't do Tun S Wes-Tys to force Tys from me).  But if you have a different specific suggestion, I'm all ears.", 'So what happens with Tys?', 'F Tys parks in Tus in this proposal, as that’s the only space available for it that is not occupied', 'I guess given your lack of response you don’t like any of my proposals or have any alternative ideas, so I’ll assume you’re *not* going to focus on getting rid of England.  That’s totally reasonable and within your rights, but then that means I have no reason to hold back, I guess.', "I am not attacking you at the moment but I also don't like the proposal.", 'So do you have another one?', 'I can withdraw from Pie if you withdraw from Tys, but not to Tus.', "I'm not sure how I can make sure you don't attack Tys if I pull back without doing a self-bounce in Tys and Ion-Tun to make sure you don't support an attack on Tys?  If I pull back, and you do Tun S Wes-Tys, you'll get in.", 'If Tus makes you uncomfortable, you could *stay* in Pie, as protection?', "That isn't much of protection since it would be easy to get through.", 'Tbf, in the long term you could push through anyway. But all I want is some buffer.', "Yeah, I get it.  I guess we could lock down on position a bit: Tys S Ion-Tun, Ion-Tun, Wes S Tun, Tun H, and that way I am not in Tus, and Tunis is locked down safely as well?  I wouldn't be pulling out if Tys in that case.", "I think that's fair. Let's go with that", "Sounds good.  I'll go set my orders before we run out of time.", 'Yeah, time limits.', "Sorry about lying about Tus/Lyo, I just had nothing left to do with those.  Couldn't just leave my units waiting around doing nothing.", "So you do realize that both Bel and Hol can get taken this fall, right?  Russia can snap up English centers at their leisure, as England isn't bothering to defend anyways.", 'And while you have no reason to trust me, Hol->Bel would mean you only lose one of those two, and since Russia has to do Mun-Ruh too cut Ruh S Hol, so if you counter-attacked: Bur s Ruh-Mun, you could possibly take Munich.', 'Seems like you do care about maintaining at least the status quo', 'between you and russia that is.', 'I can see another way in which I can not got steamrolled. You need to step up and put some pressure on Russia', 'I do realize that yes, Russia growing too big too fast is super dangerous for me', 'Since you have no reason to trust me, watch what I do.', 'And please cover your ass 🙂', 'Show me some fireworks 🧨', '🎆  big enough for you? 🎆', '(and did I not tell you about Hol+Bel?)', "(you're welcome ;P )", "You did, but I wasn't willing to make the first stab 🙂", 'oh that\'s why I said "watch I do" - I figured you had to see it to believe it.', 'So, from here, what do you plan to do with Lyo?', 'So to be honest, Tunis isn’t something you can safely hold, with England still alive and Russia on your doorstep.  So unless you have a better offer, I’ll be using Lyo to force access to Tunis, since I basically loaned it to you in the first place to get builds to attack England.', "I see, well it's true that England is about to fall", 'At least this way you can focus on that direction instead of where it’s a losing battle.', 'well that was nice of Russia to give you Munich!', "It's not something I can keep though 😦", 'Eh he has a lot of work on my account now. He may not have time to fight over Munich!']

messages:
["Good afternoon to our friends in the south, just sending this message to open a channel for future relations when ever they need to happen, and to say 'howdy and have a good game' to you.", 'Of course! I thank you very much. The future of the Kaissereich and its effect on my neighbors will be very important to me, so tell me if you want help to dissuade attack.', 'Well, should the French turn out to be a thorn in my side I would greatly appreciate the aid', 'Greetings from new Italy!', "Would just like to reiterate that Italy would likely take an opportunistic stance towards France - their defensive position is strong enough that I won't attack them proactively, but if they are locked into a conflict with you I might stab them", 'So in that sense Italy is broadly friendly to your interests - if you and France are allied I will leave you alone, but if France is your enemy I could potentially help you to break a stalemate', "But what I'd need in exchange is for you to keep me posted on developments in the west. Are you leaning towards working with England, or France?", "It seems for the moment that both are cooperative, but I'm likely to side with the French from the outset barring difficulties with them. I'll keep you posted, same relationship as previously established. In any case, friendship with the French is not very likely to last past England's demise so I'll definitely need the help then. Thank!", "Makes sense. Hopefully I'll be on the winning side of a conflict against Turkey or Austria by then, which should put us in position to squeeze France", "I'd greatly prefer you end up on Austria's side of that conflict all things considered, but if things don't go his way I wouldn't blame you for siding against them.", 'Definitely understandable. But since Italy starts off as one of the weaker countries, I basically need to play a little opportunistically', "The elephant in the room is Russia - would you have any insight on what they're planning?", "Unfortunately we only talked very briefly about staying out of each other's ways.", "Haha didn't try to hold Sweden hostage to get him to play nice with Austria? That's my usual go-to as Germany lol", 'Have you talked more with Austria? I must admit to being concerned about you moving to Tyrolia in their defense', 'Since that would allow the two of you to launch a pretty credible attack on Venetia', "As Germany I generally play somewhat more careful, get them to just promise not to be an enemy until the Western Triple becomes a Western Double. As far as Austria goes, we're allied, hence my preference for Turkey being your foe rather than them. I've no intent of turning South though, not by any means. Don't have the pieces for that.", "Yeah, fair enough. I'm planning on a pretty standard opening to Ionian Sea, aiming to convoy to Tunis and with a bounce in Austria", "It's a pretty noncommittal move, so will wait and see how things play out", "But I'm sure nobody will miss the fact that it sets me up for the Lepanto if the cards fall that wau", "Well the Lepanto setup is generally considered Italy's best opener, regardless of whether they trust Austria, hard to argue with a classic.", "It's looking like the Russians and the Turks are trying a Juggernaut.", "If they do that, we desperately need to be strongly allied with the Austrians, otherwise they'll roll us over, hard.", "I am also concerned about the Juggernaut, which pushes me towards you and Austria's camp", 'It seems France and England are at a loggerhead already, so if you side with England it might be an opportunity for me as well', "Our interests are aligned in both sides of the map, so let's just coordinate closely", "I'd be more comfortable committing both fleets east to support Austria against Turkey if I knew you were going to Burgundy (which makes it harder for France to convoy to Tuscany)", "France's F Marseille is a major headache for me", 'What say you?', "France is definitely going to be a thorn in your side, unfortunately I can neither afford to attack them right now nor likely convince them to not attack you, they're more powerful than I am and I've already pissed off two of my three potentially unfriendly neighbors.", 'The Balkan Front is pretty secure for you two though, you can at least hold and with some tricky maneuvering, very easily begin advancing through the Turks.', 'Understood. Know that Austria and Italy are not going to be able to hold out against Russia and Turkey', 'If you want to prevent a juggernaut, we will need whatever help from you we can get', "Well, as I'm sure you've noticed, I've mobilized for the task.", "I've talked to the French to try and get them off your back, but they're dedicated to seeing you off. They told me to tell you that they plan to attack Piedmont with support, which indicates that they're probably planning a convoy to Tuscany. You can't let that happen.", 'Well, it seems the attack on Piedmont with support was genuine, which seems like a very poor decision by the French', "Yeah, maybe they predicted that you'd think they were lying to me? Regardless, bad move on their part in any case, especially since you have a build.", 'Good news for you though. A distracted France is still more than enough firepower to get you through England, and it makes it easy for you to stab them after', "I don't know whether you deliberately leaked me that intel thinking I would disbelieve it and go to Tuscany, but no hard feeling if so", "That's jsut well played", "It certainly does, I wish they'd let you get on with destroying the Turks so you could focus fire on them when it's needed but still. And I gave you that information because I genuinely thought that their objective would be to get you to expect what they told me to tell you so they could do something else. Was worried that they'd do the convoy because that would be devastating for you.", 'Haha honestly that risk was very top of mind for me, since I attempted the same convoy as France in the previous game', 'So would likely have made the risk averse move to avoid the convoy even without the warning', "Yeah, it's a real power-move as the French to pull off that convoy.", "Well, it didn't work for me either", 'Well, experienced Italys generally see it coming.', 'Indeed.', "I'm trying to do damage control with the Austrians. It was incredibly damaging for them to do that and I can't imagine why they've decided to side with the Turks rather than you. If it doesn't work out, I'm going to go nuclear and split them lengthways with the Turks.", "I was taken very surprised in large part because I didn't see - and still don't see - what they stand to gain", 'And if they really stand to gain ground, why not make a play for Venice?', "No idea, the y apparently aren't interested in working with you anymore. I'm quite frankly pulling my hair over this, it's the worst possible move.", 'I find myself very confused by it as well, which is part of why I am not quite sure how to respond', "Would you be willing to coordinate against A Tyrolia? I'd be happy to support A Munich in", "I'm afraid that if I do that, my current position could quickly become untenable. I'm worried that the Austrians are planning something funky.", "Alright, so, I realize that this is a little bit late, but now that the Austrians are embroiled with the Turks, I am moving against the French. I'm trying to convince the Austrians that its in their best interests to join back with you, but I would understand if you might resent him or both of us for our failure to consistently side with you.", 'You stabbing the French is already a massive lifeline to me. I could not in good conscious ask you to do more', 'I will listen to what Austria has to say, and keep you updated on that front. I do not really trust them, but I may still be willing to work with them against the Turks if they say the right things', "I'm moving on the French this next season, hopefully they'll pull back to face me and you and the British will be able to surge back against them.", "I'm pleasantly surprised that you're so willing to work with England as well", "In that case i'll play defensively but try to set myself up for a counteroffensive", "Well the English are a little miffed that I didn't move last season, but still, I see no reason not to work with them for the time being.", 'Yeah, agreed. The English are too desperate to turn down your support', 'Conversely, you have a free walk into Paris right now', 'Since France has only fleets', 'A Mun - Bur and then to Paris is guarrenteed to succeed as long as you can cover a potential stab on Mun, which you could easily do with A Ber', "And then A Hol-Bel isn't quite as foolproof, but is pretty safe as well", 'Especially if you support yourself into NTH and move Kie - Hol', "If you're wondering who convinced the French to make it a fleet, you need go no further", 'Well, sounds like things are in good shape!', 'Hopefully the French are sufficiently distracted that you can launch a counter attack.', "Yeah, I'll make the most of this", "The Austrians wouldn't happen to be talking about me, would they?", "I haven't heard anything from them", "Well, at the very least that's good. I'm worried about them potentially deciding that they want Warsaw, despite the fact that I'm on the right side of a stalemate line where they'd only get 1 supply center if they attacked.", 'Are you coordinating with the Turks? I think that for the time being that would be a good idea.', 'Yeah, am trying to do so', 'Not to be needy or anything, but I would greatly appreciate a hard move for Venice this next year.', 'I will make a play for Venice this Fall', "If I was in Austria's shoes, I would do a self bounce of F Ven - Tri, A Ser - Tri", 'So I plan to do F Alb S F Ven - Tri, A Apu - Ven', 'Odds of succeeding in this improve dramatically if also support with A Tyr S A Apu - Ven - would you be willing to do so?', 'Gas and Bur likely cannot take Mar anyways, so in my view you would be better off using:
A Par & A Pic S A Gas - Bre
F NTH S F Bel - ENG
A Bur - Mun', "This would be a near-guarantee that you take Brest and would occupy F ENG as a consolation prize in the only outcome where you didn't, while still covering Munich", 'My only problem with that plan is that it risks losing Burgundy if the French pull a fast one and go for Silesia instead, while moving Marseilles into Burgundy.', "That's a valid point. My view is that A Mar - Bur is unlikely but A Boh - Sil is a real risk", 'If you want to keep France out of Bohemia, A Gal is the only unit you have that can do so', 'Which might be a better investment that using it to try and snipe Bud', 'Although actually, if you hit Vienna and France has two disbands, they may struggle to keep up the pressure around Silesia', "That's true, I don't know if I want to take my chances with that though.", "I'll probably move into Vienna, but I'm not sure I can afford to move out of Burgundy.", 'Understood, So then you would use A Gal to cover Warsaw, A Bur to cover Munich, and then try to snipe Vienna with A Tyr?', 'Correct']
