messages:
["Good afternoon, I think it's important that you and I come to terms over a few things right here at the start, including the fate of Belgium and how despite our situation as naturally suited antagonists, Britain is the larger threat to both of us.", 'Hey Germany. "Natural suited antagonists"? I beg to differ. I personally think that over here in the west, a France/Germany alliance is the strongest, preferably taking out England ASAP. What do you think?', "I spoke to England and they don't seem like a particularly diplomatic player, but I'm pretty sure I can get into the English channel. From there I would like to move to Belgium, since they will most likely be moving back to London. In return for Belgium I would be willing to support or convoy you into English territory.", "Well, England hasn't spoken to me just yet, so it sounds like perhaps they won't intend to be friendly with me whatsoever. I think that your plan sounds pretty solid, I'll support you into Belgium if need be.

 I only say Natural Antagonists because that's how it frequently goes, notwithstanding the strength of the alliance. I personally find it quite strong, and not nearly as asymmetrical as alliances between either of us and the Brits.", 'Taking the English down ASAP is definitely something on my agenda though, one less front line to worry about.', "Great. I'll move the the English channel. What are you thinking for moves?", 'Mostly just pivoting toward the low countries, Kiel to Denmark and probably to the North Sea from there.', 'Sounds good.', "So you're headed to Belgium now from the Channel, yes?", "That would be ideal. It's a bit of a gamble, but England will probably will think I'm going to Lon. It would be greatly appreciated if you supported me in but you don't have to. I don't know what else Ruh would do though...", "Eh, the English say they're moving to London, no need for the support; I need to send some troops over East, don't trust the Russians.", "I don't trust the French not to try to play me for a patsy and you're far more communicative anyways, might as well tell you stuff that'll give you the upper hand.", '*English', "Fuckin' brain getting words mixed up and making me look sus. >.>", "Ruhr is moving back to Munich to deploy east, regardless. The Russians bouncing the Austrians in Galicia indicates that they're going to do a Juggernaut and I have to do everything I can to stymie that.", 'and... you really trust england?', 'They are most likely not telling the truth', 'But ok sounds good', "No, I don't, but I think they'd be idiots to do anything else. But if you're really worried, I can support you in and keep the pivot to the East for next year.", 'I would try to get into Englands territory with your fleet', "No, it's fine, don't support", "I intend to, but I can't leave Denmark till it's secured without putting myself way out of position for anything in the east if the Russians get aggressive. You sure you don't want the support?", "No, of course I want the support, as it can't possibly help me and adds an extra layer of protection. I just thought you brought up a fair point about russia, and it's your choice, so I'm not going to argue with you a ton about what you should do.", "To be honest I wouldn't be to worried about Russia. They didn't even move towards you, and after hearing what you said I talked with Austria, and they said they were going to attack Russia, so I don't think there is an alliance there. I would instead invest in capturing english territory, which would give you troops to build in your homeland and defend against Russia if they choose to attack you.", "Fair enough, I'll focus on the English first then.", 'Ok, and will you be supporting me into Burgundy? Up to you.', 'You mean Belgium? Sure, nothing better to do for the time being.', 'Yes, belgium. Oops', "Well, I didn't hit the button to update the orders, but it worked out just fine anyways I suppose.", 'My bad.', "Yes, it's fine. Sooo, ig the game is in grace period, so I was wondering what you builds were looking like. I will build a fleet in Bre and if you build a fleet in Kiel, the 4 combined fleets should be more than enough to take out britain, and we shouldn't have to build anything else in that regard.", "I'm building a fleet in Kiel. Most of my armies are going to move East to counter the Juggernaut that's actively happening over there, but I'll dedicate one army and both fleets to dropping the English.", 'great', 'What are you thinking about moves? We should coordinate', "Moving into Helgoland Bight, probably moving into Sweden with Britain's help while I can still manipulate them into thinking I'm their friend rather than their foe (Kill two birds with one stone, you know), two armies move East.", "Alright, we have a good chance of making it into the North Sea if you support Helgoland Bight into it with both fleets. Unfortunately it seems the British called my bluff early and the Russians have committed to taking Sweden, so things aren't exactly ideal, but we're still in a pretty definitively winning position.", 'Russians really fucked me up by not bouncing me in Sweden. Good move on their part.', "Hey Germany. It's a shame Russia called your bluff. I will support helgoland into nth with both of my fleets. We should have a 100% chance of getting in if you attack Nwy with sweden and cut support. This is the best move for sweden in any scenario, as that territory is basically lost, and who knows, maybe england will move Nwy to Stp and you will end up getting Nwy", 'Yeah, the only worry is that England will move North Sea to Denmark, which would be a damn shame and a pain in my ass.', "And if they're displaced they could *retreat* there, which would just add insult to injury.", "Ah, good point. I don't have anything for Pic to do, do you think I should have Eng convoy it over to whales? Or do you think it would be more useful to support you in", 'Also, would you mind telling italy the following: "Hey Italy. You probably know I have an alliance with france, and they have troops right next to you. They told me that they were going to support themselves into Piedmont. I'm letting you know because I'm worried about them getting too strong and stabbing me, as they already have 6 centers." Or something like that, just in your own words. I want them to think I'm supporting myself into Piedmont.', "Picardy can stay put for now, I think that the English will anticipate us doing something other than trying to take the North Sea and will move to prevent it, if they think we're thinking far enough ahead. It's worth the gamble that they'll only throw one support at it. Besides, in all likelihood even if you tried to move to Wales, Yorkshire would block it, since Yorkshire isn't doing anything useful where it is now.", "Will do, can't guarantee they'll believe me though.", 'Sent it along, in my own words.', 'thx mate', "What do you think I should do in the med with italy? I could either move LYO to WES, hoping to bounce them there(why I had you send that message), and have Mar attack Pie, or I could just support myself in and if they do go to WES i'll move my fleet in the English channel down to cover spain/portugul", "If you convoyed from Spain to Tuscany it'd be all over for them, effectively.", 'Everything worked exactly as planned it seems!', 'yep.', 'Only worry now is where the Brits will retreat to.', "Im pretty confident they can't retreat to denmark, because it was contested this turn", "They can't, but they can retreat to SKA", "So what do you think would be the best move? You think England's going to try to dislodge North Sea with all their navies or do you think they'll want to cover Edinburgh more?", "i really don't know.", 'I think I will support Nth with belgium, but convoy Pic to whales', "Good idea, even if we lose North Sea that'll get us into the isles, then it's game over for them.", "that's the idea", "Ok, it's a shame we lost the north sea but it was inevitable, at least we got whales. England should be gone in a few turns and then I can focus all my energy on Italy.", 'If we continue to trust each other, communicate, and play well I think we have a two-way victory in the bag', 'Next turn I can support you into Nth again, and you will definitely get it, since I have the army in whales to cut support', 'Try to suck up as many of russias supply centers as you can, they are very weak and seem to be afk', "Yeah, hopefully, if all goes well, I'll be building quite a lot. Austria's betrayal of Italy in favor of Turkey is really telling so I think I'll have my hands full on that front soon enough. A two way victory sounds splendid to me.", 'How will we split Britain?', "Um, so this turn I think I'm going to support myself into london, but also support you into the Nth sea. From there you can take Edi, and I can support you into that.", "Nah, focus on succeeding in London, poke North Sea with Belgium so that it can't support. I'm supporting myself into Sweden and moving on Norway from there; if you want to simplify things we could have you take all of Britain and just transfer Belgium to me (So that we both net 2 from the British, since I'll have Norway), though I would understand why you might be uncomfortable with that.", "I'm really torn over what to do in Italy. I spoke to Austria about going after them together, and they are thinking about it. I could try convoying Mar into Tuscany, with Pie supporting. This is basically the same as just moving Pie into Tuscany, with support from my fleet, except for that if I convoy Mar the support is less likely to be cut(I think there is a higher chance they will cut support to my fleet than cut support/move to Piedmont)", "The Austrians are currently making a whole slew of bad decisions, allying with the Turks is a sucker's bet. I'm not sure what you should do tbh, the Italians aren't talking to me much anymore.", "I suppose we could have me take all of Britain, and have me give you Belgium, but I would ask that as soon as you take Belgium, you move back out. It's definitely an option, but I will have to think about it.", "Oh of course, once I had it I'd get out of there immediately. Trust is the key in transfers like this.", "Take your time, we've got several turns until it needs settling, and several days till the next turn.", "I could move Piedmont to Tyr, it's a great place to be. Not sure if I would get in though.", "Tyr is one of those spots where everyone around gets nervous when you're there.", "Yep, Austria wouldn't like that.", 'Good tactical utility though, if you want to strongarm into Venice.', "I feel like we could very well end up with a standoff between me and you, and turkey and austria. I'm kinda trying to brew unrest over there, spreading rumours and such.", "I have been desperately attempting to convince the Austrians that they're better off with me but it hasn't  been working.", "Why didn't you want me supporting you? My move into Lon was already garunteed.", 'Whatever', 'I was thinking either the British or Russians would make a play for Sweden, wanted the support to ensure the move. In any case we should have an easy time moving forward.', "In any case we're both making pretty good gains.", "I'll be building in Munich, just so I don't catch you by surprise with that. Want to be able to move in as fast as possible on the Austrians when we go for it.", 'What do you think the next move should be?', 'Could you support Bel to Nth?', "Absolutely. My fleet in Denmark wouldn't be doing anything otherwise. Are you moving in with Piedmont or Tyrolia? Because if it's not Tyrolia I can support that to stay put, just in case the Austrians get antsy.", "I'm having Tyrolia support piedmont in. I will definitly get it unless for some reason the austrians support italy, which would be wierd.", 'Thanks for supporting Bel', "Feel free to support Tyr, but don't feel pressure to do so if you have a better move in mind", "I'm waiting to have St. Petersburg to make a move on the Austrians, Munich has nothing to do for the moment except to support Tyrolia.", 'Everything worked out great.', 'And it looks like the Turks and Austrians are at each others throats now.', 'The Brits are trying really hard to get me to throw myself against you. I mean reeeeeally hard.', "lol. All I can say is that I hope you don't, since we have this game in the bag", 'You could use that. Tell them you will stab me, and tell them my moves(but false) so that I can get in more easily', 'I can probably jump into Edinburgh via the Norwegian sea this next year, no need for the Belgium transfer.', 'LOL italy just messaged me and said that "Austria's build in Trieste cannot be anything but a play for Venice" and then "I am willing to concede it to you if you cooperate elsewhere", so I guess they don't understand I already have it. They sure are getting desperate.', 'Think I should play along, or just tell them about what "concede" really means, and that you can't concede something if your opponent controls it and you have no chance of getting it back.', 'Also, what do you think I should do for builds? A fleet in Brest or an army in Paris?', "Go ahead, play along lol, should be interesting. If I were you I'd build fleets, the enemy from here on out is one on the seas almost exclusively.", 'k, what do you think about builds?', 'Would you be ok with me building army in paris? I would send it over to the south east prob', "Not sure, at least one army, might build a navy even though I won't have much use for it anymore.", "You can if you want, but I think a Navy would do a lot to forcing the Mediterranean open faster. Italy's a huge traffic jam for armies.", 'Do you still want belgium? At this point our borders are like, super demiliterized, which is pretty nice, but at this point I do trust you, if you want to have it. If you want an center it would prob be better for you to have belgium than enland. Or do you even want a center, since you already have 1 more than me.', "Well, I certainly wouldn't say no, you'll definitely have an easier time taking the Italians than I will bleeding anything from the Austrians.", "Whoa, didn't realize we were so close to adjudication. What are you thinking for moves?", "I don't need support from you anywhere this turn. All my units will be making moves at englands centers/taking the med/taking italy", "All I can say is that I REALLY hope you don't betray me, since you have some units looking like they could just walk into my supply centers. We have such a good run going right now, as long as you don't betray me we can definitly get a two-way draw", "I think I'm gonna move on the Austrians, take them out while they're distracted with the Turks.", 'England and Italy both are truly desperate to get me to turn on you, and even the Austrians have thrown some urgings in lol', 'lol yes, the Austrians hate me for staying in Triest when I told them I would move, Italy has been desperatly begging for DMZ, and England is obviously done.', "Right, and Austria can't possibly take me and Turkey at the same time", 'As long as we keep austria and turkey fighting, you can run them down by land and I can apply presure with fleets', "Yeah, I'm playing both sides to keep them at each other's throats.", 'great', "For the record I really hate doing crap like this but I told myself right at the start that I needed to gussy up and go for a solo for once in my life. I love this game but ironically hate the deception aspect >.>

In any case it's nothing personal and you were super cool to work with", "Tbh I was pretty sure you would do that, but (for once) I wanted to trust somebody in this game bc I've been known to backstab people like crazy. Your all good, Imma put up a fight though and try to stop you 😉", 'You were cool to work with to', 'Good luck. We did have the two way draw in the bag though', 'Wow, you really are pouring units into my hometown. Basically leaving Austria and turkey alone, huh', "I know we did, and to be honest I've been super wishy washy about actually going through with this because of that. I almost did it last turn. I still feel like a jerk doing it.", "And yeah, as long as they're at each other's throats they aren't too much threat, unless you pull some silver tongue on them to get a real coalition of the willing going", "Silver toung it is. It's going to be pretty great if I can get them to organize then we can actually win against you and that would be cool. Well see", "That would be exceptionally interesting! I wouldn't have a lot of chance to shore up that flank, it'dbe a fair and square win. In any case, good luck, and sorry about this, again.", 'Your good, I (almost definitly) would have done the same.', "I normally don't, just because I feel like actually being trustworthy most of the time generally improves the game culture. Or maybe I'm just soft and making excuses, hard to say lol", '🤷‍♂️', 'Well this next turn is going to be weird as hell, however it turns out.', 'An outstanding move on your part by the way, the Italians and British are not being as enthusiastic of Revanchists as I was hoping.', 'What do you mean outstanding move?', 'as in which one 😏', 'The one where you somehow convinced the English to side with you, mostly.', 'That coalition finally came through, maybe just in time as well.']

messages: ['How’s it going Russia?', "Hi Austria, how's your relationship with Turkey?", 'Pretty basic so far, how about you?', 'Ouch, so aggressive', 'Living for the bounce!', 'I could say the same thing to you', 'How’s that?', 'rumania is yours if you want it!', 'Sounds good!']

messages: ['Hi there england! We haven’t talked yet', "we have not.  I think i'm most interested in what your stance on Russia and Germany are.  Particularly Germany.  I'm not sure I can trust them yet.", 'They have been nice to me but have not really wanted to share their plans unfortunately.', 'Me and him are both worried about russia though, there are rumors of a juggernaut forming.', 'I don’t think russia and I will get along, he hasn’t wanted to talk and then he attacked Gal so not a good start to the relationship.', 'I’d be curious about your views on Germany and Russia as well', 'Willing to chat?', 'hello?', "i think my messages didn't go through during the mess up", 'we need to join together againt germany', 'I was wondering why you didn’t respond', 'So what do you think? I see you’re busy gobbling up Russia but France and Germany will quickly get strong and we need to prepare for their march East.', 'I mean there isn’t much I can do this season']

messages: ['Hello Turkey!', 'Hi! So often, Austria gets jumped from the get go.  I’d prefer that not to happen, since Turkey is usually next. Also, where’s the fun in that?', 'Yeah I’d love not to get jumped! Have you heard from Russia much', 'No , not yet. Thought he might be the unknown party.', 'I finally got a message', 'What do you think about supporting me into Rum, either I get Rum and lose Ser or it bounces. Either way we keep russia from a build and I net 1 build either way', 'That sounds like a great idea. Serbia will be the mover?', 'Yes', 'Have you talked with russia much do you think they’re full on trying to attack me?', 'I could also support you if you want to do it that way. Then you could get an extra build if it worked', "I think it would be better for you to take Rumania than I.  And my gut tells me that your neigbors are looking to gang up on you.  That's not good for me, since I'm still stuck in this corner. 😦", 'Which neighbors?', 'Germany.', "Italy isn't too friendly towards you right now.", "And I haven't really talked with Russia yet.", "Let's talk '02.  Let's say you take Rumania.  That will leave Serbia and Greece open.  Who gets what?", 'I get Serbia you get Gre? That would leave us at 2 and 2', 'that is a fair swap.', 'Okay great, I’ll head into Rum then', 'Well we don’t trust each other', "well, Russia told me that he was going to bounce me in the black sea.  I figured, what's the worst that could happen?  you bounce him in Rumania?  If i support you in, you only get one build.  So, since you said you were cool with me having greece in the long term, why not go for it in the short term?", "yeah, I didn't talk to you about going to greece, but ... this isn't chutes and ladders.  \n\nHowever, we're now in really good position to make short work of Russia if we work together.  Thoughts?", 'Yeah I would love support into Rum, how would you eventually wanna divide things?', "I get Greece.  And then we split Italy.  Also, I'd appreciate a boost into Sevastapol, but the rest of Russia would be yours.", "The trick will be getting to Italy before France does.  What would help is if Italy would head West towards France.  That'll leave his back door open for us.  Maybe if you told him that you didn't have any interest in helping against Turkey and that he should make a go another direction, but ... then again ... after bouncing in Trieste twice in a row, he might not be super interested in working with you.", 'We arranged bouncing in Tri, I might be able to convince him since France build that fleet in Mar', 'Which unit do you want supported into Rumania?', 'I’ll move Ser in', 'Are we still good?', 'Yes.', 'I’m cutting Sev and supporting ser-rum. I assume since I haven’t heard anything from Russia he thinks he’s working with you.', 'I’d support yourself to hold in Galicia, but you might have other designs for your units.', 'If you think I should then I will', 'Either that or keep being aggressive.', 'It’d be nice to bounce him in Ukraine and force a retreat off the board.', 'I’m sorry I didn’t trust you, everything I was seeing made me feel like you were allied with Russia', 'Hmmm. Where do we go next?', 'Well I guess my first question is whether or not you still trust me. You can ask Italy or Germany, I thought I saw a juggernaut forming and that would have been the end of my game. I had to play it safe especially since you switched moves on me last fall.', 'I understand how you could say the same about me but I’m in the more vulnerable position.', 'It’s possible that you could take Rum this turn if Russia doesn’t defend it. They seem like a bit of a wild card so who knows what they will decide to do. You could go for that on your own and when you see that I don’t attack you this season you might be able to trust me enough to move this forward.', 'I think ... I think you have Budapest vulnerable. I’d appreciate it if UKR either went for Moscow or Sevastopol.   We have to worry about the Western Triple.', 'So, let’s get our armies into Russia and counter Germany there.', 'Do you think you can get me into Sev?', 'Like can you commit BLA to supporting me in', 'Well, that fleet is busy attacking Rumania.  I would like a build, which I think is fair.', 'What is Serbia doing?  Maybe Serbia can support me into Rumania?', 'I think I need to protect my homeland with Ser', "But ... me trusting you, after you lied to me ... that's a tall order.  I'm not closed off to it, but I'd like to know if you know what the Italian is planning on doing.", 'I understand that you would want a build, but then there is no reason for me to attack Sev', 'Well, SEV could be supporting GAL back to Rumania.', 'Well to be completely honest we were gonna attack you because I was convinced that you were allied with Russia so I have some stuff to figure out', 'I think our first order is deciding what we think russia is gonna do', "I know that it doesn't benefit you any, and I think your better move it to go for Moscow.", 'I might be able to convince Italy to back up since they have the French to deal with', 'I would appreciate that.', 'Game moves tonight at midnight right', 'I think that Russia is probably on the weaker end of the spectrum.  I think that he goes defensive.', 'He might lash out at Vienna, but it is extremely unlikely that he goes for Budapest while you move to Vienna.', 'I think, honestly, that he supports himself back into Rumania and covers Moscow.', "Which is why I was requesting that you go for Sevastopol, cutting it's support.", 'That would be the smart move, he seems irrational though. He doesn’t really negotiate and is very aggressive', "yes, I don't disagree.  I'm a little disappointed that you thought I was going to blindly ally with him!", 'What do you think Italy is going to do with A Greece?', 'was he supposed to support you into Bulgaria?', 'He just offered but I’m explaining to him that you attacked Russia last turn, he didn’t realize', "I've asked him to allow us to go after Russia while he gets into a better position against France.  We need to drive a wedge into this Western Triple.", "Ok, I now realize that there's no Western Triple.  Instead, it's an FG - which is just as bad for you guys, since Germany is already into Russia.  Here's my idea, and take it or leave it ... but I suggest that he keep rotating his fleets out (maybe move towards WES and TUN) while you backfill ION.  He builds a fleet in ROM and you convoy him into NAP in the Spring.  Now he's got three fleets in play while France is trying to land a unit on England.  Meanwhile, you move your army out of SER and towards Munich and I move BUL/RUM north into SEV, MOS, and WAR.  It's a logical expansion for all of us and presents each of us with room to grow and peace in the Balkans.", 'I’m gonna have to think about it because so far germany has been a good friend for me this game', 'Right.  And where is he going to go next?', 'And when you say good friend ... what supply centers did he help you into?  🙂', 'Totally understandable, just has been giving good information and stuff. Right now his plan is to eat France after england (could be a lie but I would believe it)', 'Right ... with what units?', "France has three armies.  If he gets into England, he'll get more builds.  Unless you're going to help him get past FRance in the south, he'll have armies in France for defense.  And if you're anti-Italy ... then we should be having a totally different conversation!", 'I\'m not saying that you should sign up 100% for the "go after Germany" party.  But, I\'ve presented you with a fair proposal and it doesn\'t require you to do anything that\'s against your interests.  And if it can clear up your border in the south, it can let you access "where the dots are," which for you - is Germany.', 'I gotcha, I’ve gotta eat dinner right now but how late tonight will you be able to chat', "I'll be around.  Either on the computer or on my phone.", 'Okay I’m reading your proposal again and are you saying you would get all of russia?', 'I now realize what I wrote, but I do need an outlet.  If you want to see me nothing but bottled up, and without an outlet for expansion ... we need to have another kind of conversation.', 'Not without exchanging some of those centers for Rumania and/or Bulgaria.', "I'm also totally down with attacking through Italy and pouring fleets into the Med.  But, I am under the impression that you want to ally with him and want to find some way to work together with you.", 'I do not want you bottled up, bottled up turkey usually attacks Austria.', 'I agree with that sentiment.', 'What would your thoughts be if I could get Germany to support Ukr into War', 'I think that would be awesome', 'it would be difficult to defend, but is the right move for you.  worry about holding it later, get the bulwark against his growth now.', 'Okay we’ll go ahead with that then', 'What will happen with Serbia and Greece?', 'Not sure, what would you vote for', "Well, I'd prefer it if you didn't cut Bulgaria's support of an attack on Rumania.", 'Of course not, I was probably just gonna support gre holding', 'If you trust italy not to go after Serbia, then you could rotate your armies out (and probably bounce in one/both of them).', 'Yeah still figuring that it', 'Out', 'Is he sending his fleet to EMS or towards France?', "Well, you know which direction I'd prefer.", 'I’m hoping toward France, I told him he should', "I've enjoyed speaking with you, by the way.", 'I hope that we can continue to have these kinds of dialogues.', 'Yeah you as well, it’s good to find people that are actually able to negotiate and stuff. I hope we can get past our early struggles', 'do you play any face-to-face?', 'Not much, hard to get 7 people together', "Where abouts do you live (general area, I'm not trying to cyberstalk you)?", 'I go to Michigan state', "there's a sizeable hobby in Chicago", "But I don't think East Lansing is THAT close.", 'Haha no it is not', "I went to college in Cleveland and could never get a game together.  I did travel to tournaments, though.  They're a lot of fun as long as you can get over yourself and realize that every game is an opportunity to improve.", 'How do tournaments work?', "Three to four, more or less random, board draws.  Usually you score your best three results.  There are a few different scoring systems, but generally speaking - if you get good results, you'll do well.", 'Seems fun, how do the negotiations go? Like do you pull people aside', "yes, usually it's in a big room - like a hotel ballroom or dormitory basement", "and there's 3-5 boards going on simultaneously", "so, there's about 10-30 conversations going simultaneously.", 'Okay so people know who you’re talking to, that is one thing I like about this is like I could be talking to russia and you wouldn’t know it', 'Obviously I’m not in this case', 'Or maybe you are ....', 'Hahahaha', "By the way, if Serbia isn't moving, can it support CON-RUM?", 'It’s moving', 'May I ask where?', 'Bud', "I'll trust you on this one.", 'Italy has gotten himself way out of position. I know you like him, but ... he’s not taking advantage of his opportunity against France and is wide open to attack by us. You could go to Greece and I could go to Rumania and we’d have peace. (I’d have to hold for a turn, so that he doesn’t retreat to Bulgaria).', 'Yeah let’s look at the builds first', 'I’m also a little frustrated with him because he hasn’t replied to a single one of my messages in days (not that I’m overloading him, but this needs to be a two way conversation - I mean, that’s what we’re being compensated for!).', 'Yeah he hasn’t chatted a ton with me either', '🤷\u200d♂️', "you around?  I'm weighing my build options.", 'any thoughts?  Fleet versus Army?', 'Alright. We doing this?', 'My bad, didn’t see the notifications', 'So obviously you’re gonna kick Italy out of your area, are you gonna take Sev this turn?', 'Well, I’d like to coordinate my move with you. Are you taking Greece? He’d be down to one Army and since he doesn’t seem interested in defending his dots from France, you and I might as well go after them.', 'Honestly I have to decide how much I trust you vs how much faith I have in him. Because at this point in the game I still need an ally.', 'I’d like for you to take Sev, it we need russia to lose more units so that we can finish him before germany is too strong.', 'I feel like despite our rocky start you and I have communicated enough that we can declare a full alliance though', 'Regarding Sev, I’d like to take it this year. Maybe in the Fall?', 'I think we can definitely partner up and work together to both our benefit. I also don’t think it will be particularly difficult to separate our forces. I only have two armies, so I’m not much of a threat to you and you only have one fleet - so I’m not worried about you coming after me by yourself. The wild card in all of this is Italy, and he’s only got one fleet over by me and a French unit in Piedmont.', 'Right now I have Bulgaria supporting Serbia into Greece. I’ll rotate up the coast towards Sevastopol in the Fall and we’ll convoy you onto the boot as soon as possible. I mean ... that’s a strong position for you.', 'If we were to follow this sort of path where do you see your expansion going? You can get Sev, Tun, and Nap, then what', 'Also I don’t need your support into Gre, I would rather you took Sev this turn', 'Expansion: maybe mos and STP? I’m assuming you’re going to head west towards Germany in this scenario. Otherwise, this is only a 10 year game, I don’t have grand designs on a solo victory or anything.', 'Ok. I will hold in Bulgaria so that Italy can’t retreat there. And I’ll take out Sev. You’re not dislodging Galicia, are you? I’m worried about him retreating to Rumania.', 'Sounds good, I am not dislodging', 'OK.', "I know you're choosing between working with Italy and working with me.  The path I'm offering to you allows you to control your own growth and depend on yourself for gains - and making it so that our border is unit-less.  The path of working with Italy also allows you to grow, but you'll be depending on someone else for help after the initial gain and you'll have to dedicate units to the balkans until I'm fully eliminated from the game.   Both are legitimate choices, but I think my offer is superior based on merit.  I've demonstrated that I'm a reliable partner, that I make solid moves and do what I say.", 'Yeah I gotcha, I just hate playing as austria and don’t have a lot of successful experience. Often due to Turkey. That and the beginning of this game has made me cautious.', 'But Italy’s attack on you is uncoordinated with me and not really going anywhere and it’s hard to work with that', 'I’m curious what your plan is. You have a lot of armies on my border.', 'Yeah I gotta move those, I’m sorry I was just playing cautious. Hopefully Russia has actually quit that would make things much easier. I will definitely have to go cover Tri because Italy is in Ven and pissed at me', 'I’m moving EMS-ION. Can you support it in with Greece?', '(EAS)', 'Yes', 'Will you support me into años', 'Mos', 'I was gonna self bounce in Rumania', 'Is Germany kicking you out of Warsaw?', 'No but we’re trying to transfer it, it was a condition of me getting it first', 'I can’t this year. He’s got that pesky A Galicia', 'Okay it’s all good', 'Hey, I wanted to say - is it something you need to prevent the loss of a center? Because if Germany is going to start trying to take dots off of you, you need help into Moscow more than I need to guarantee I don’t lose Rumania. In fact, I can just cover Rum with Bulgaria. You’re not going to stab me for one dot, I certainly hope.', 'I am not, yeah I was gonna make that argument but wait until we got closer to when moves were due', 'And yes that would help guarantee that I don’t lose one', 'So how’s that sounding', "Ok.  I'm down for working together for mutual benefit.  I'd appreciate it if you began moving your units away from my dots.", 'Was planning on it', 'Glad I trusted you. I think we’re past the awkward phase of our relationship.', 'I hope so, now I need to make sure france is just doing what they did to get into Ven', 'Or end around on Germany', 'That would be a premature stab', 'might be his last real chance.', "how do you want to proceed?  Can you support ION to hold?  I'd like to convoy my army into Apulia.  We can gut Italy like a trout, if that's what you'd like to do.  Otherwise, we could look at getting you back into Warsaw.  Is Germany where you want to head next?", 'I kinda have to take care of Italy first so that front is secured', 'Ok. Are you ok with the convoy to Apulia?', 'Yeah of course', 'Or do you want Italy all for yourself! 😊', 'No we could use the help!', 'Are you cool with me displacing the last Russian troop so that we don’t have to deal with it', 'Also have you reached out to France about your move?', 'Let me look at the map.', 'And I’m not sure it’s a good idea to tell France what my plans are regarding Italy. I don’t think he’s interested in sharing the prize.', 'I mean, sure. Which unit is going in? I can support it.', 'And you can focus on grabbing STP or getting position on Warsaw or Munich.', 'Gal is going in', 'And France asked me to coordinate so it’s possible that he would want to with you', 'Are you coordinating with him? I’d just dislodge Tyrolia - if he retreats into Munich, that’s a win for you. If he takes Venice, we’ll get you in there in the Fall.', 'Not really coordinating no', "Ok, cool.  I don't really need to know, and I'll find out in two hours, but I'm wondering if you'll have two units on Venice in the fall - giving us three.", 'I’m still not sure', 'Ughhh. This is going to be a slog. I guess we’ll be trading centers while Germany and France get bigger. 🤷\u200d♂️', 'Well this will be fun', 'Unnecessary, though.', 'Your call.', 'Because it’s highly unlikely France will get to me before Germany comes for you.', 'When you wish washed on Venice and suggested collaboration with France, I changed all my orders.', 'I only did it because I didn’t trust you, I would have trusted you if you had built that army in Smy', 'Ok. You never once said anything to me bout it.', 'Didn’t want you to be on to me knowing', "I'm sad, because it feels like I lost a friend.  I really enjoyed talking and strategizing with you.", 'We really couldn’t trust each other, we both stabbed on the same turn twice', "what other stab?  Are you referring to Fall '01?  Because I think it's impossible to stab someone in '01.", 'Probably what I’m talking about it. How is it impossible? We both went back on an agreement', '1901 is the feeling out year.', 'I’d have to look back and see what year I’m thinking of but does it really matter', "Ok, so here's the thing.  One of two things is going to happen. Germany is going to come after you (unlikely) or Germany is going to pour into France (much more likely).", "But, with either scenario, I'm not sure how productive a land war with me is going to be for your long term survival.", 'Agreed, I honestly don’t think I can win this game', 'well, neither of us is going to solo in 6 years.', 'Germany ... could.', 'All he needs is Moscow and one of your centers/Marseilles.  Because he has fleet superiority in the north and Italy just took a unit off the board.', "Not probable, but possible.  but it makes sense, he's giving me the hard sell to attack you and offering all sorts of long term assistance.", 'Yeah I think he’s gonna solo unless France attacks him', "France can't attack him.", 'what is FRance going to attack him with?', 'I’m not saying like this season', 'I mean, literally, what is he going to attack him with.', 'his fleets?', 'Wow yeah he does have way too many fleets', 'Look, we\'re not so stuck fighting each other.  I think we both can admit that neither of us is going to "win" this game.  But, I\'d really prefer not to "lose" the game to  a solo.', 'So what do you propose', 'That we get you into Warsaw.', 'I\'m being 100% serious.  My orders right now are for a full scale attack on you.  But I\'m willing to change them to be cooperative if I feel like you\'re being honest with me and are actually open to working together.  I also don\'t "need" to get a dot right now and am willing for you to gain - if it\'s off of Germany.', "I will change SEV to supporting MOS to hold.  UKR will support RUM-GAL, and I suggest you try to get into BOH so that you can cut SIL's support of WAR to hold.", 'I could be wrong, and Germany could not go after FRance and instead go after you full bore.  If he does, these are EXACTLY the orders you need to use anyway.  But this prevents the solo by Germany.  Which he could get if you and I fight.  It would be close, but France is totally incompetent and does not have the units to mount an actual defense.  If France had build an Army in Paris, this would be a totally different conversation.  But he built a fleet in Brest.', "You could also take advantage of the situation to re-position your fleet to threaten Venice and take advantage of the French-German situation, but that's your call.  I'd appreciate it if you didn't try to take advantage of this situation and come at me full bore, but - even if you did come at me strong, I'm not sure you gain much.", "And you would risk A LOT by exposing your back to Germany.  Because if you do come after me, you can be damn sure I'm helping him into Moscow and anywhere else I can.", 'Yeah I’ll try and come up with the best moves for me, I would be willing to try and work with you because even if you’re lying to me I was gonna lose anyways', 'I’m hoping you realize that as well.', 'We have time before the next orders are due', 'Germany is asking for support into Moscow.', 'So, he might be setting up for a move into Galicia. He’s not really being open about his moves.', 'Interesting', 'So ... what do you want to do?', 'Good morning!', 'Okay I’m sorry I haven’t been around, you able to talk?', 'What lies were you going to waste my time with on a Sunday evening?', 'None, you told me that you currently had an all out attack planned on me until we talked and then we were never able to talk', 'I admit that it was kind of my fault we never talked but I couldn’t have faith that you changed your orders since we hadn’t talked', 'Go after Warsaw, I’ll build fleets and DMZ our borders. Harass me, and I’ll be a headache for you.', '// I’m disappointed in you. Not in your moves, but that you’ve being compensated to communicate with other players and you’re apparently comfortable taking money for something and not doing it. That speaks volumes about you. /:', 'I literally told you my orders. You chose to ignore them.', 'That seems a bit dramatic', '🤷\u200d♂️ I’m interested to see if Germany can solo here. It’ll be close.', 'I mean I still would acknowledge that we should not fight if we want any chance at winning', 'But are we ever gonna trust each other', 'You never stopped lying to me. Show me the good faith moves you never actually made, and I’ll leave you to fight off Germany. But, I know that you’re just bullshitting me in order to marginally improve your position against me.', 'I know man I’m honestly sorry', 'I hate Austria and am terrible at playing it. I can’t ever trust anyone and freak out every time I play as them. I’ve been a dick this game because of it', "I see ... I see that you can't help yourself.  Go after Germany, stop coming after me.", 'I don’t know what that means', 'Enjoy your disband. You should have taken the free dots in Warsaw and Moscow.', 'Would you mind keeping Germany from getting a solo?', 'Planning on it', 'Good luck. Can’t see how he’d stop you  I’m going to continue a defensive play. Your commitment to the anti-turkey strategy is impressive', 'You’re so full of it!', 'You have plenty of easy centers, and you still relentlessly attack me!', 'If you’re going to throw the solo, be definitive about it! Support him into your own centers and be done with it! Or have a “if you don’t do X, I’ll do Y,” where why is throw the solo.', 'But be rational, I’m not going to just give you my dots!', 'I truthfully don’t think that he is going to solo', 'I will stop attacking you if you move on Warsaw and Vienna.', 'Moscow is his 18th', 'Fuck it yeah I’ll attack him, believe me if you want I know you have issues with it and I don’t blame you', 'I’ve felt, for a while, that your best possible result was peace with Italy and me to stop Germany.  So, I want to believe you. I won’t attack you any more.', 'I’m supporting myself to hold. I ask that you play defense.', 'And grab a German dot.', 'You can take Sev', 'I think I have to. Can you support me into UKR and support Italy into Tyrol?', 'I can’t support you but I can support him', "why can't you support me?  what else would A Warsaw be doing?", 'nicely done.  nicely, nicely done.', "The key to not losing to the solo is - assuming the loss of Portugal (which is two coin flips) - not losing 2 of the 3 Russian centers.  You're going to lose STP.  The question then becomes, how to we preserve Warsaw?  My recommendation is: \nA: VIE S TYR - BOH\nA: WAR - UKR\nA: STP - MOS\nA: BUD - GAL\nI: TYR - BOH\nI: TRI - TYR\nI: VEN - PIE\nI: TUS S VEN - PIE\nT: SEV - UKR\nT: RUM S WAR - UKR\nT: ANK - SEV (Convoy)\n\nThis plan destroys UKR or ensures that we control it.  It places units in places that they can cut supports on Warsaw which dramatically increases our odds of taking it back if we loose it or maintaining it if we don't.  Chances are, if STP is dislodged, it will be able to retreat to LVN.    Worst case is that Germany just rotates his armies north - supporting himself into LVN and getting three on Warsaw (LVN, PRU, and SIL.  But, we'll either be in Moscow or Galicia (probably both) and Ukraine.  We'll also have two on Munich and he can either keep munich or go after Warsaw.\n\nThe other option is to support ourselves into Galicia and Ukraine.  I'm willing to do as you suggest.", 'I like your first plan with the moves all laid out', 'Sorry for taking so long', 'I should have supported you into Ukraine.', 'It is what it is', 'I flipped a coin. It was wasn’t an effort to weaken you.']

messages: ['Hey Austria, how are you?', 'Good how about you', 'Wow big moves into ENG', 'Eh, kinda typical opening', 'England upset about it?', 'They seem fine, obviously not going to be to great of a relationship from this point out though.', 'Yeah, how about germany? I’ve been talking to him a decent amount. He is very chatty but doesn’t seem to give away much', 'I would agree with that. Me and Germany are on good terms', 'would you be interested in going after Italy with me?', 'Not right now no, I have to figure out my russia and turkey situation', 'Looks like you and germany are allied? Good luck versus england', 'Thanks. I would like you to re-consider my proposal. You have become a very powerful country, and if you decide to turn on Italy, there is nothing they can do between the two of us. Right now Turkey and Russia are standing each other off, and there is no immediate threat from either of them for you. Italy will be easy supply centers. I would of course support you into their territory, provided you return the favor. We could work out more details if your interested', 'I have to check the board more, I need to balance attacking Russia while handling Italy. Also turkey and I are currently friendly but who knows when he will change his mind', 'But yes we should at least communicate', 'so... what do you think?', 'I can’t commit to a full attack yet, if Russia is MIA again then I should be able to', 'k', 'Just wanted you to know, my move into Tyr is not at all meant aggresivly at you. I am only going to use it to strong-arm into venice', 'I am hoping that is true, would have been good of you to talk about it with me', 'Wanna talk about Italy?', 'sure', "Would you be willing to support Tyr to venice? In return I will support you into one of italys centers in the future. This move will also get my troop out of  Tyr, which, understandably, you don't like", "You know what, on second thought, it's fine. I can make it into venice on my own, by poking tuscany with LYO", 'Okay sounds good, either way I’ll be happy to see Tyr moved!', "Ok, I didn't think Germany would betray me but they did. No matter what situation your in, we have to all start working together to stop Germany or they will win.", 'Sending this to everyone btw', 'You and Turkey are the most importand. Italy and England are basically out of the game anyways. We can definitly still stop germany, but in order for that to happen you and Turkey are going to have to stop fighting, right away, and work together to get in through germanies back door. They are sending basically all of their units to my hometown, which means they are going to be vulnerable against you guys.', 'Understood, you’re gonna have to be a go between with me and turkey though because he hates me', 'Agreed. I will talk to him more now', 'Ok, I spoke with turkey and they are on board. So the plan is for you to send some units over to germany, where you could get some free builds, while all of their units are occupied with attacking me']

messages: ["Hello Russia, we should discuss Scandinavia and Germany.  I think that's where we will be overlapping.  Have you decided where you stand with germany?", "Hi England - We are friendly right now, trying to figure out where they're headed. Can we split Sweden and Norway up North and leave it at a truce for now?", 'it seems germany and France are teaming up against me.  Do you think we can work together against Germany?', "I don't know, 2 fleets east seems pretty hostile to Russia to me!!", 'Well if it makes you feel any better I’ll be using a fleet to take Norway and my second fleet is covering London.', 'perfect, so right on track for our norway-sweden split up north. Happy to aid in the fight against germany and france as well', 'Great to hear', 'What’s with the hold in barents???', 'can you not support germany in sweden this round?', 'Id plan to move army, so its not going anywhere once it gets there', 'Yeah but you could have supported me into Denmark. We are both in bad positions right now. We need to work together better.', "sure thing, but you're the one whose been supporting germany up until now..."]

messages: ['How’s it going? I usually bounce in the Black Sea but am always open to doing something else with your fleet.', "I hope you're doing well.  i'm a little under the weather myself, i was at a board game convention all weekend and I think I got a ConCough.", "Oh no, I'm sorry to hear that! I too usually do in the black sea bounce, and old habits might die hard.", 'All good in the neighborhood', 'I’ll stay out of Armenia.', 'Appreciate it!', "How's your relationship with Italy and Austria? If you're leaning towards attacking one over the other, I'd be interested in teaming up", "I'd prefer to make a go at Austria first, then I'll crank out fleets and deal with Italy.", "I find Austria and Italy's opening moves to be... interesting.", 'Shall we bounce in the black sea again?', '"bounce bounce bounce bounce bounce bounce bounce"', 'What are you thinking re Austria? (Hopefully, it\'s not "they\'re my best friends against russia!")', 'Germany will help take care of Austria if we want to team up', 'Do you want Germany getting part of Austria?', 'But I like the overall concept of ya working together. The RT alliance is a strong one.', 'the ya was a typo.  I like the overall concept of US working together. 🙂', "I'm a little surprised to be in the Black Sea, to be honest.  I thought we were going to bounce there.  What are your feelings on it?   From my perspective, I have no plans on attacking you but I'd rather be in it that have you in it.", '(I thought we were going to bounce there because of what you wrote, which was "bounce bounce bounce bounce bounce bounce bounce.")', 'A gift from me to you, as a sign of goodwill', "Well, I have no issue with you guaranteeing your build in Rumania.  I take it you trusted the Austrian not to go to Galicia, would you like support to hold it against the (I assume) three armies he's about to have facing it?  Obviously, this depends on his build, but i assume it's going to be A BUD.", 'I’m surprised you didn’t build in a Moscow. What are your thoughts about Galicia?', 'You need help or are you planning something else?', 'sorry was off the grid with no internet for the large chunk of the weekend!', 'im hoping nothing hostile is coming my way', 'i have no intention of extending south, so i think our natural alliance should continue', 'It would seem that everyone ganged up on you simultaneously.', 'Sometimes that will happen when no one hears from a player for days.  Any thoughts on our current situation?', 'hard when you work at government and cant have phone for 10 hours a day, then night skool!', 'I too work in a SCIF.', 'last week I had the flu, though - so plenty of time for chit chatting with the college kids we seem to be playing with.', 'Mind if I take Rumania?', 'Scif life!!', 'Rumania is all yours, be my guest', "Thanks.  I won't take Sevastopol until you say it's ok.  I've got an Austro-Italian problem and I thought I could buy off the Austrian, but he seems to be dead set on attacking me.", 'Thank you again for Rumania.  My offer on Sev still stands.', 'Are you still with us?', 'Hello?']

messages: ["Hey England, how are you? I would like to discuss an England/France alliance with you, aimed at taking Germany out quickly. I think if we work together and can trust each other, this could be an amazingly strong alliance. No matter what you decide, I think it would be in both our favor's to leave the English Channel as a DMZ. Let me know if you're interested and we can coordinate moves.\nLooking forwards to a great game, and good luck!", "Hello France, I too am interested in moving east with you and I think a channel DMZ is a great idea.  I'll be doing a fairly standard English opening so let's see how russia and germany open to plan tactics next season.", 'Sounds good', "I'm going to do a standard opening too, MAO, Spain, and burgundy", 'Stab out the gate? Interesting tactics.', 'Haha, sorry. Maybe we can work together sometime in the future(if you were willing to trust me😂 ). Good luck though.', "Ok, I didn't think Germany would betray me but they did. No matter what situation your in, we have to all start working together to stop Germany or they will win.", 'Sending this to everyone btw', 'Are you going to back off?', 'how do you feel about supporting me into the north sea?', 'will do, with both fleets.', 'I was going to support myself in, but this actually works out a lot better', 'I thought you were supporting me in! What happened? We gotta get him out of N Sea', 'oh god, i totally forgot about that. i honestly meant to. the 14 days just made me forget', 'So what now?', "I'm supporting you into Nth with one fleet", "i clearly didn't get this message in time", "i think thats it, we're toast"]
